129 // exclude unsupported compilers
130 #if defined(__clang__)
131 #if (__clang_major__ * 10000 + __clang_minor__ * 100 + __clang_patchlevel__) < 30400
132 #error "unsupported Clang version - see https://github.com/nlohmann/json#supported-compilers"
133 #endif
134 #elif defined(__GNUC__) && !(defined(__ICC) || defined(__INTEL_COMPILER))
135 #if (__GNUC__ * 10000 + __GNUC_MINOR__ * 100 + __GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__) < 40900
136 #error "unsupported GCC version - see https://github.com/nlohmann/json#supported-compilers"
137 #endif
138 #endif

142 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
143 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
144 #endif

152 // allow for portable deprecation warnings
153 #if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__GNUG__)
154 #define JSON_DEPRECATED __attribute__((deprecated))
155 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
156 #define JSON_DEPRECATED __declspec(deprecated)
157 #else
158 #define JSON_DEPRECATED
159 #endif

161 // allow to disable exceptions
162 #if (defined(__cpp_exceptions) || defined(__EXCEPTIONS) || defined(_CPPUNWIND)) && !defined(JSON_NOEXCEPTION)
163 #define JSON_THROW(exception) throw exception
164 #define JSON_TRY try
165 #define JSON_CATCH(exception) catch (exception)
166 #else
167 #define JSON_THROW(exception) std::abort()
168 #define JSON_TRY if (true)
169 #define JSON_CATCH(exception) if (false)
170 #endif
171 
172 // override exception macros
173 #if defined(JSON_THROW_USER)
174 #undef JSON_THROW
175 #define JSON_THROW JSON_THROW_USER
176 #endif
177 #if defined(JSON_TRY_USER)
178 #undef JSON_TRY
179 #define JSON_TRY JSON_TRY_USER
180 #endif
181 #if defined(JSON_CATCH_USER)
182 #undef JSON_CATCH
183 #define JSON_CATCH JSON_CATCH_USER
184 #endif

186 // manual branch prediction
187 #if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__GNUG__)
188 #define JSON_LIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(!!(x), 1)
189 #define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(!!(x), 0)
190 #else
191 #define JSON_LIKELY(x) x
192 #define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) x
193 #endif

207  template <template <typename, typename, typename...> class ObjectType, \
208  template <typename, typename...> class ArrayType, \
209  class StringType, class BooleanType, class NumberIntegerType, \
210  class NumberUnsignedType, class NumberFloatType, \

229 #define NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(type) \
230  template <typename T> \
231  struct has_##type { \
232  private: \
233  template <typename U, typename = typename U::type> \
234  static int detect(U&&); \
235  static void detect(...); \
236  \
237  public: \
238  static constexpr bool value = \
239  std::is_integral<decltype(detect(std::declval<T>()))>::value; \
240  }

285 // implementation of C++14 index_sequence and affiliates
286 // source: https://stackoverflow.com/a/32223343
287 template <std::size_t... Ints>
288 struct index_sequence {
289  using type = index_sequence;
290  using value_type = std::size_t;
291  static constexpr std::size_t size() noexcept
292  {
293  return sizeof...(Ints);
294  }
295 };
296 
297 template <class Sequence1, class Sequence2>
298 struct merge_and_renumber;
299 
300 template <std::size_t... I1, std::size_t... I2>
301 struct merge_and_renumber<index_sequence<I1...>, index_sequence<I2...>>
302  : index_sequence<I1..., (sizeof...(I1) + I2)...> {
303 };
304 
305 template <std::size_t N>
306 struct make_index_sequence
307  : merge_and_renumber<typename make_index_sequence<N / 2>::type,
308  typename make_index_sequence<N - N / 2>::type> {
309 };
310 
311 template <>
312 struct make_index_sequence<0> : index_sequence<> {
313 };
314 template <>
315 struct make_index_sequence<1> : index_sequence<0> {
316 };
317 
318 template <typename... Ts>
319 using index_sequence_for = make_index_sequence<sizeof...(Ts)>;

321 /*
322 Implementation of two C++17 constructs: conjunction, negation. This is needed
323 to avoid evaluating all the traits in a condition
324 
325 For example: not std::is_same<void, T>::value and has_value_type<T>::value
326 will not compile when T = void (on MSVC at least). Whereas
327 conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, T>>, has_value_type<T>>::value will
328 stop evaluating if negation<...>::value == false
329 
330 Please note that those constructs must be used with caution, since symbols can
331 become very long quickly (which can slow down compilation and cause MSVC
332 internal compiler errors). Only use it when you have to (see example ahead).
333 */
334 template <class...>
335 struct conjunction : std::true_type {
336 };
337 template <class B1>
338 struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {
339 };
340 template <class B1, class... Bn>
341 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...> : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {
342 };
343 
344 template <class B>
345 struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, not B::value> {
346 };
347 
348 // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
349 template <unsigned N>
350 struct priority_tag : priority_tag<N - 1> {
351 };
352 template <>
353 struct priority_tag<0> {
354 };

365 
366 template <typename T>
367 struct is_complete_type<T, decltype(void(sizeof(T)))> : std::true_type {
368 };

370 NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(mapped_type);

375 template <bool B, class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
376 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {
377 };
378 
379 template <class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
380 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl<true, RealType, CompatibleObjectType> {
381  static constexpr auto value =
382  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::key_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
383  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::mapped_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
384 };
385 
386 template <class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleObjectType>
387 struct is_compatible_object_type {
388  static auto constexpr value = is_compatible_object_type_impl<
389  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleObjectType>>,
390  has_mapped_type<CompatibleObjectType>,
391  has_key_type<CompatibleObjectType>>::value,
392  typename BasicJsonType::object_t, CompatibleObjectType>::value;
393 };
394 
395 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
396 struct is_basic_json_nested_type {
397  static auto constexpr value = std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::iterator>::value or
398  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_iterator>::value or
399  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::reverse_iterator>::value or
400  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_reverse_iterator>::value;
401 };
402 
403 template <class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleArrayType>
404 struct is_compatible_array_type {
405  static auto constexpr value =
406  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleArrayType>>,
407  negation<is_compatible_object_type<
408  BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
409  negation<std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t,
410  CompatibleArrayType>>,
411  negation<is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
412  has_value_type<CompatibleArrayType>,
413  has_iterator<CompatibleArrayType>>::value;
414 };
415 
416 template <bool, typename, typename>
417 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl : std::false_type {
418 };
419 
420 template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
421 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl<true, RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType> {
422  // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
423  using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
424  using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
425 
426  static constexpr auto value =
427  std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
428  CompatibleLimits::is_integer and
429  RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
430 };
431 
432 template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
433 struct is_compatible_integer_type {
434  static constexpr auto value =
435  is_compatible_integer_type_impl <
436  std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
437  not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value,
438  RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType > ::value;
439 };
440 
441 // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
442 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
443 struct has_from_json {
444  private:
445  // also check the return type of from_json
446  template <typename U, typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<void, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(
447  std::declval<BasicJsonType>(), std::declval<T&>()))>::value>>
448  static int detect(U&&);
449  static void detect(...);
450 
451  public:
452  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(
453  detect(std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
454 };
455 
456 // This trait checks if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&) exists
457 // this overload is used for non-default-constructible user-defined-types
458 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
459 struct has_non_default_from_json {
460  private:
461  template <
462  typename U,
463  typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<
464  T, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(std::declval<BasicJsonType>()))>::value>>
465  static int detect(U&&);
466  static void detect(...);
467 
468  public:
469  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
470  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
471 };
472 
473 // This trait checks if BasicJsonType::json_serializer<T>::to_json exists
474 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
475 struct has_to_json {
476  private:
477  template <typename U, typename = decltype(uncvref_t<U>::to_json(
478  std::declval<BasicJsonType&>(), std::declval<T>()))>
479  static int detect(U&&);
480  static void detect(...);
481 
482  public:
483  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
484  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
485 };
486 
487 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleCompleteType>
488 struct is_compatible_complete_type {
489  static constexpr bool value =
490  not std::is_base_of<std::istream, CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
491  not is_basic_json<CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
492  not is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
493  has_to_json<BasicJsonType, CompatibleCompleteType>::value;
494 };
495 
496 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleType>
497 struct is_compatible_type
498  : conjunction<is_complete_type<CompatibleType>,
499  is_compatible_complete_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleType>> {
500 };

555 class exception : public std::exception
556 {
557  public:
559  const char* what() const noexcept override
560  {
561  return m.what();
562  }
563 
565  const int id;
566 
567  protected:
568  exception(int id_, const char* what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {}
569 
570  static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id_)
571  {
572  return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
573  }
574 
575  private:
577  std::runtime_error m;
578 };
579 
623 class parse_error : public exception
624 {
625  public:
634  static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg)
635  {
636  std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
637  (byte_ != 0 ? (" at " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") +
638  ": " + what_arg;
639  return parse_error(id_, byte_, w.c_str());
640  }
641 
651  const std::size_t byte;
652 
653  private:
654  parse_error(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const char* what_arg)
655  : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_) {}
656 };
657

701  return invalid_iterator(id_, w.c_str());
702  }
703 
704  private:
705  invalid_iterator(int id_, const char* what_arg)

851 namespace nlohmann

856 // JSON type enumeration //
858 
883 enum class value_t : std::uint8_t {
884  null,
885  object,
886  array,
887  string,
888  boolean,
889  number_integer,
890  number_unsigned,
891  number_float,
892  discarded
893 };
894 
905 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept
906 {
907  static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 8> order = {{
908  0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */,
909  1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */, 2 /* unsigned */, 2 /* float */
910  }};
911 
912  const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
913  const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
914  return l_index < order.size() and r_index < order.size() and order[l_index] < order[r_index];
915 }
916 } // namespace detail
917 } // namespace nlohmann

936 // #include <nlohmann/detail/meta.hpp>
937 
938 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
939 
940 namespace nlohmann
941 {
942 namespace detail
943 {
944 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
945 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
946  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
947  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
948  int> = 0>
949 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
950 {
951  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
952  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
953  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
954  break;
955  }
956  case value_t::number_integer: {
957  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
958  break;
959  }
960  case value_t::number_float: {
961  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
962  break;
963  }
964 
965  default:
966  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
967  }
968 }
969 
970 template <typename BasicJsonType>
971 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t& b)
972 {
973  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_boolean())) {
974  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
975  }
976  b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
977 }
978 
979 template <typename BasicJsonType>
980 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::string_t& s)
981 {
982  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_string())) {
983  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be string, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
984  }
985  s = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::string_t*>();
986 }

1006 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename EnumType,
1007  enable_if_t<std::is_enum<EnumType>::value, int> = 0>
1008 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, EnumType& e)
1009 {
1010  typename std::underlying_type<EnumType>::type val;
1011  get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
1012  e = static_cast<EnumType>(val);

1015 template <typename BasicJsonType>
1016 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t& arr)
1017 {
1018  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1019  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1020  }
1021  arr = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::array_t*>();
1022 }
1023 
1024 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
1025 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
1026  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1027 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l)
1028 {
1029  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1030  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1031  }
1032  std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(),
1033  std::front_inserter(l), [](const BasicJsonType& i) {
1034  return i.template get<T>();
1035  });
1036 }
1037 
1038 // valarray doesn't have an insert method
1039 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1040  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1041 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::valarray<T>& l)
1042 {
1043  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1044  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1045  }
1046  l.resize(j.size());
1047  std::copy(j.m_value.array->begin(), j.m_value.array->end(), std::begin(l));
1048 }
1049 
1050 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1051 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/)
1052 {
1053  using std::end;
1054 
1055  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1056  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType& i) {
1057  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1058  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1059  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1060  });
1061 }
1062 
1063 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1064 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
1065  -> decltype(
1066  arr.reserve(std::declval<typename CompatibleArrayType::size_type>()),
1067  void())
1068 {
1069  using std::end;
1070 
1071  arr.reserve(j.size());
1072  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1073  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType& i) {
1074  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1075  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1076  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1077  });
1078 }
1079 
1080 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1081 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, std::array<T, N>& arr, priority_tag<2> /*unused*/)
1082 {
1083  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i) {
1084  arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1085  }
1086 }
1087 
1088 template <
1089  typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1090  enable_if_t<
1091  is_compatible_array_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1092  not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::array_t,
1093  CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1094  std::is_constructible<
1095  BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>::value,
1096  int> = 0>
1097 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr)
1098 {
1099  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1100  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " +
1101  std::string(j.type_name())));
1102  }
1103 
1104  from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<2>{});
1105 }
1106 
1107 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
1108  enable_if_t<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
1109 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleObjectType& obj)
1110 {
1111  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object())) {
1112  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1113  }
1114 
1115  auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
1116  using value_type = typename CompatibleObjectType::value_type;
1117  std::transform(
1118  inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(),
1119  std::inserter(obj, obj.begin()),
1120  [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const& p) {
1121  return value_type(p.first, p.second.template get<typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
1122  });
1123 }
1124 
1125 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
1126 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
1127 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
1128 // an arithmetic type?
1129 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1130  enable_if_t<
1131  std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1132  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
1133  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
1134  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
1135  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1136  int> = 0>
1137 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1138 {
1139  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
1140  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
1141  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1142  break;
1143  }
1144  case value_t::number_integer: {
1145  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1146  break;
1147  }
1148  case value_t::number_float: {
1149  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1150  break;
1151  }
1152  case value_t::boolean: {
1153  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
1154  break;
1155  }
1156 
1157  default:
1158  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1159  }
1160 }
1161 
1162 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename A1, typename A2>
1163 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::pair<A1, A2>& p)
1164 {
1165  p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};
1166 }
1167 
1168 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
1169 void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, Tuple& t, index_sequence<Idx...>)
1170 {
1171  t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
1172 }
1173 
1174 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
1175 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::tuple<Args...>& t)
1176 {
1177  from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...>{});
1178 }
1179 
1180 struct from_json_fn {
1181  private:
1182  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1183  auto call(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const
1184  noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
1185  -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void())
1186  {
1187  return from_json(j, val);
1188  }
1189 
1190  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1191  void call(const BasicJsonType& /*unused*/, T& /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept
1192  {
1193  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1194  "could not find from_json() method in T's namespace");
1195 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1196  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1197  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1198  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1199  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1200 #endif
1201  }
1202 
1203  public:
1204  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1205  void operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const
1206  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<from_json_fn>().call(j, val, priority_tag<1>{})))
1207  {
1208  return call(j, val, priority_tag<1>{});
1209  }
1210 };
1211 } // namespace detail
1212 
1216 namespace
1217 {
1218 constexpr const auto& from_json = detail::static_const<detail::from_json_fn>::value;
1219 }
1220 } // namespace nlohmann

1314  {

1316  j.m_value = arr;
1317  j.assert_invariant();

1320  template <typename BasicJsonType>
1321  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t&& arr)

1324  j.m_value = std::move(arr);

1327 
1328  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1329  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleArrayType, typename BasicJsonType::array_t>::value,
1330  int> = 0>
1331  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleArrayType& arr)
1332  {
1333  using std::begin;
1334  using std::end;
1335  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1336  j.m_value.array = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::array_t>(begin(arr), end(arr));
1337  j.assert_invariant();
1338  }
1339 
1340  template <typename BasicJsonType>
1341  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::vector<bool>& arr)
1342  {
1343  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1344  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1345  j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
1346  for (const bool x : arr) {
1347  j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
1348  }
1349  j.assert_invariant();
1350  }
1351 
1352  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1353  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<T, BasicJsonType>::value, int> = 0>
1354  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::valarray<T>& arr)
1355  {
1356  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1357  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1358  j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
1359  std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
1360  j.assert_invariant();
1361  }
1362 };

1514 struct to_json_fn {
1515  private:
1516  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1517  auto call(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const noexcept(noexcept(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val))))
1518  -> decltype(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)), void())
1519  {

1521  }
1522 
1523  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1524  void call(BasicJsonType& /*unused*/, T&& /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept
1525  {
1526  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1527  "could not find to_json() method in T's namespace");
1528 
1529 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1530  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1531  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1532  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1533  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1534 #endif
1535  }
1536 
1537  public:
1538  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1539  void operator()(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val) const
1540  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<to_json_fn>().call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1>{})))
1541  {
1542  return call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1>{});
1543  }
1544 };
1545 } // namespace detail
1546 
1548 namespace
1549 {
1550 constexpr const auto& to_json = detail::static_const<detail::to_json_fn>::value;
1551 }
1552 } // namespace nlohmann

1579 
1591 struct input_adapter_protocol {
1593  virtual std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() = 0;
1595  virtual void unget_character() = 0;
1596  virtual ~input_adapter_protocol() = default;
1597 };
1598 
1600 using input_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<input_adapter_protocol>;
1601 
1611 class input_stream_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1612 {
1613  public:
1614  ~input_stream_adapter() override
1615  {
1616  // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
1617  // maintain ifstream flags
1618  is.clear();
1619  }
1620 
1621  explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i)
1622  : is(i), sb(*i.rdbuf())
1623  {
1624  // skip byte order mark
1625  std::char_traits<char>::int_type c;
1626  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xEF) {
1627  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xBB) {
1628  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xBF) {
1629  return; // Ignore BOM
1630  } else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof()) {
1631  is.unget();
1632  }
1633  is.putback('\xBB');
1634  } else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof()) {
1635  is.unget();
1636  }
1637  is.putback('\xEF');
1638  } else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof()) {
1639  is.unget(); // no byte order mark; process as usual
1640  }
1641  }
1642 
1643  // delete because of pointer members
1644  input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
1645  input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
1646 
1647  // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
1648  // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
1649  // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
1650  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() override
1651  {
1652  return sb.sbumpc();
1653  }
1654 
1655  void unget_character() override
1656  {
1657  sb.sungetc(); // is.unget() avoided for performance
1658  }
1659 
1660  private:
1662  std::istream& is;
1663  std::streambuf& sb;
1664 };
1665 
1667 class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1668 {
1669  public:
1670  input_buffer_adapter(const char* b, const std::size_t l)
1671  : cursor(b), limit(b + l), start(b)
1672  {
1673  // skip byte order mark
1674  if (l >= 3 and b[0] == '\xEF' and b[1] == '\xBB' and b[2] == '\xBF') {
1675  cursor += 3;
1676  }
1677  }
1678 
1679  // delete because of pointer members
1680  input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
1681  input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
1682 
1683  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
1684  {
1685  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor < limit)) {
1686  return std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type(*(cursor++));
1687  }
1688 
1689  return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
1690  }
1691 
1692  void unget_character() noexcept override
1693  {
1694  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor > start)) {
1695  --cursor;
1696  }
1697  }
1698 
1699  private:
1701  const char* cursor;
1703  const char* limit;
1705  const char* start;
1706 };
1707 
1708 class input_adapter
1709 {
1710  public:
1711  // native support
1712 
1714  input_adapter(std::istream& i)
1715  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
1716 
1718  input_adapter(std::istream&& i)
1719  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
1720 
1722  template <typename CharT,
1723  typename std::enable_if<
1724  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
1725  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
1726  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
1727  int>::type = 0>
1728  input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
1729  : ia(std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), l))
1730  {
1731  }
1732 
1733  // derived support
1734 
1736  template <typename CharT,
1737  typename std::enable_if<
1738  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
1739  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
1740  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
1741  int>::type = 0>
1742  input_adapter(CharT b)
1743  : input_adapter(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b),
1744  std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b)))
1745  {
1746  }
1747 
1749  template <class IteratorType,
1750  typename std::enable_if<
1751  std::is_same<typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category, std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
1752  int>::type = 0>
1753  input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
1754  {
1755  // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
1756  // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
1757  assert(std::accumulate(
1758  first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
1759  [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val) {
1760  res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
1761  return res;
1762  })
1763  .first);
1764 
1765  // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
1766  static_assert(
1767  sizeof(typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
1768  "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
1769 
1770  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last));
1771  if (JSON_LIKELY(len > 0)) {
1772  // there is at least one element: use the address of first
1773  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&(*first)), len);
1774  } else {
1775  // the address of first cannot be used: use nullptr
1776  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(nullptr, len);
1777  }
1778  }
1779 
1781  template <class T, std::size_t N>
1782  input_adapter(T (&array)[N])
1783  : input_adapter(std::begin(array), std::end(array))
1784  {
1785  }
1786 
1788  template <class ContiguousContainer, typename std::enable_if<not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
1789  std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag, typename std::iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value,
1790  int>::type = 0>
1791  input_adapter(const ContiguousContainer& c)
1792  : input_adapter(std::begin(c), std::end(c))
1793  {
1794  }
1795 
1796  operator input_adapter_t()
1797  {
1798  return ia;
1799  }
1800 
1801  private:
1803  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
1804 };
1805 } // namespace detail
1806 } // namespace nlohmann

1837 template <typename BasicJsonType>
1838 class lexer
1839 {
1840  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
1841  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
1842  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
1843  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
1844 
1845  public:
1847  enum class token_type {
1848  uninitialized,
1849  literal_true,
1850  literal_false,
1851  literal_null,
1852  value_string,
1853  value_unsigned,
1854  value_integer,
1855  value_float,
1856  begin_array,
1857  begin_object,
1858  end_array,
1859  end_object,
1860  name_separator,
1861  value_separator,
1862  parse_error,
1863  end_of_input,
1864  literal_or_value
1865  };
1866 
1868  static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
1869  {
1870  switch (t) {
1871  case token_type::uninitialized:
1872  return "<uninitialized>";
1873  case token_type::literal_true:
1874  return "true literal";
1875  case token_type::literal_false:
1876  return "false literal";
1877  case token_type::literal_null:
1878  return "null literal";
1879  case token_type::value_string:
1880  return "string literal";
1881  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
1882  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
1883  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
1884  return "number literal";
1885  case token_type::begin_array:
1886  return "'['";
1887  case token_type::begin_object:
1888  return "'{'";
1889  case token_type::end_array:
1890  return "']'";
1891  case token_type::end_object:
1892  return "'}'";
1893  case token_type::name_separator:
1894  return "':'";
1895  case token_type::value_separator:
1896  return "','";
1897  case token_type::parse_error:
1898  return "<parse error>";
1899  case token_type::end_of_input:
1900  return "end of input";
1901  case token_type::literal_or_value:
1902  return "'[', '{', or a literal";
1903  default: // catch non-enum values
1904  return "unknown token"; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
1905  }
1906  }
1907 
1908  explicit lexer(detail::input_adapter_t adapter)
1909  : ia(std::move(adapter)), decimal_point_char(get_decimal_point()) {}
1910 
1911  // delete because of pointer members
1912  lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
1913  lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
1914 
1915  private:
1917  // locales
1919 
1921  static char get_decimal_point() noexcept
1922  {
1923  const auto loc = localeconv();
1924  assert(loc != nullptr);
1925  return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
1926  }
1927 
1929  // scan functions
1931 
1947  int get_codepoint()
1948  {
1949  // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
1950  assert(current == 'u');
1951  int codepoint = 0;
1952 
1953  const auto factors = {12, 8, 4, 0};
1954  for (const auto factor : factors) {
1955  get();
1956 
1957  if (current >= '0' and current <= '9') {
1958  codepoint += ((current - 0x30) << factor);
1959  } else if (current >= 'A' and current <= 'F') {
1960  codepoint += ((current - 0x37) << factor);
1961  } else if (current >= 'a' and current <= 'f') {
1962  codepoint += ((current - 0x57) << factor);
1963  } else {
1964  return -1;
1965  }
1966  }
1967 
1968  assert(0x0000 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
1969  return codepoint;
1970  }
1971 
1987  bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<int> ranges)
1988  {
1989  assert(ranges.size() == 2 or ranges.size() == 4 or ranges.size() == 6);
1990  add(current);
1991 
1992  for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range) {
1993  get();
1994  if (JSON_LIKELY(*range <= current and current <= *(++range))) {
1995  add(current);
1996  } else {
1997  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
1998  return false;
1999  }
2000  }
2001 
2002  return true;
2003  }
2004 
2020  token_type scan_string()
2021  {
2022  // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
2023  reset();
2024 
2025  // we entered the function by reading an open quote
2026  assert(current == '\"');
2027 
2028  while (true) {
2029  // get next character
2030  switch (get()) {
2031  // end of file while parsing string
2032  case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): {
2033  error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
2034  return token_type::parse_error;
2035  }
2036 
2037  // closing quote
2038  case '\"': {
2039  return token_type::value_string;
2040  }
2041 
2042  // escapes
2043  case '\\': {
2044  switch (get()) {
2045  // quotation mark
2046  case '\"':
2047  add('\"');
2048  break;
2049  // reverse solidus
2050  case '\\':
2051  add('\\');
2052  break;
2053  // solidus
2054  case '/':
2055  add('/');
2056  break;
2057  // backspace
2058  case 'b':
2059  add('\b');
2060  break;
2061  // form feed
2062  case 'f':
2063  add('\f');
2064  break;
2065  // line feed
2066  case 'n':
2067  add('\n');
2068  break;
2069  // carriage return
2070  case 'r':
2071  add('\r');
2072  break;
2073  // tab
2074  case 't':
2075  add('\t');
2076  break;
2077 
2078  // unicode escapes
2079  case 'u': {
2080  const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
2081  int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
2082 
2083  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1)) {
2084  error_message = R"(invalid string: '\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits)";
2085  return token_type::parse_error;
2086  }
2087 
2088  // check if code point is a high surrogate
2089  if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF) {
2090  // expect next \uxxxx entry
2091  if (JSON_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u')) {
2092  const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
2093 
2094  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1)) {
2095  error_message = R"(invalid string: '\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits)";
2096  return token_type::parse_error;
2097  }
2098 
2099  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
2100  if (JSON_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF)) {
2101  // overwrite codepoint
2102  codepoint =
2103  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
2104  (codepoint1 << 10)
2105  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
2106  + codepoint2
2107  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
2108  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
2109  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
2110  - 0x35FDC00;
2111  } else {
2112  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2113  return token_type::parse_error;
2114  }
2115  } else {
2116  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2117  return token_type::parse_error;
2118  }
2119  } else {
2120  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF)) {
2121  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
2122  return token_type::parse_error;
2123  }
2124  }
2125 
2126  // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
2127  assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
2128 
2129  // translate codepoint into bytes
2130  if (codepoint < 0x80) {
2131  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
2132  add(codepoint);
2133  } else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF) {
2134  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
2135  add(0xC0 | (codepoint >> 6));
2136  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2137  } else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF) {
2138  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2139  add(0xE0 | (codepoint >> 12));
2140  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2141  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2142  } else {
2143  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2144  add(0xF0 | (codepoint >> 18));
2145  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F));
2146  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2147  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2148  }
2149 
2150  break;
2151  }
2152 
2153  // other characters after escape
2154  default:
2155  error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
2156  return token_type::parse_error;
2157  }
2158 
2159  break;
2160  }
2161

2297 
2298  // U+0080..U+07FF: bytes C2..DF 80..BF
2299  case 0xC2:
2300  case 0xC3:
2301  case 0xC4:
2302  case 0xC5:
2303  case 0xC6:
2304  case 0xC7:
2305  case 0xC8:
2306  case 0xC9:
2307  case 0xCA:
2308  case 0xCB:
2309  case 0xCC:
2310  case 0xCD:
2311  case 0xCE:
2312  case 0xCF:
2313  case 0xD0:
2314  case 0xD1:
2315  case 0xD2:
2316  case 0xD3:
2317  case 0xD4:
2318  case 0xD5:
2319  case 0xD6:
2320  case 0xD7:
2321  case 0xD8:
2322  case 0xD9:
2323  case 0xDA:
2324  case 0xDB:
2325  case 0xDC:
2326  case 0xDD:
2327  case 0xDE:
2328  case 0xDF: {
2329  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF}))) {
2330  return token_type::parse_error;
2331  }
2332  break;
2333  }
2334 
2335  // U+0800..U+0FFF: bytes E0 A0..BF 80..BF
2336  case 0xE0: {
2337  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0xA0, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2338  return token_type::parse_error;
2339  }
2340  break;
2341  }
2342 
2343  // U+1000..U+CFFF: bytes E1..EC 80..BF 80..BF
2344  // U+E000..U+FFFF: bytes EE..EF 80..BF 80..BF
2345  case 0xE1:
2346  case 0xE2:
2347  case 0xE3:
2348  case 0xE4:
2349  case 0xE5:
2350  case 0xE6:
2351  case 0xE7:
2352  case 0xE8:
2353  case 0xE9:
2354  case 0xEA:
2355  case 0xEB:
2356  case 0xEC:
2357  case 0xEE:
2358  case 0xEF: {
2359  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2360  return token_type::parse_error;
2361  }
2362  break;
2363  }
2364 
2365  // U+D000..U+D7FF: bytes ED 80..9F 80..BF
2366  case 0xED: {
2367  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x9F, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2368  return token_type::parse_error;
2369  }
2370  break;
2371  }
2372 
2373  // U+10000..U+3FFFF F0 90..BF 80..BF 80..BF
2374  case 0xF0: {
2375  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x90, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2376  return token_type::parse_error;
2377  }
2378  break;
2379  }
2380 
2381  // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
2382  case 0xF1:
2383  case 0xF2:
2384  case 0xF3: {
2385  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2386  return token_type::parse_error;
2387  }
2388  break;
2389  }
2390 
2391  // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
2392  case 0xF4: {
2393  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x8F, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2394  return token_type::parse_error;
2395  }
2396  break;
2397  }
2398 
2399  // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
2400  default: {
2401  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
2402  return token_type::parse_error;
2403  }
2404  }
2405  }
2406  }
2407 
2408  static void strtof(float& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
2409  {
2410  f = std::strtof(str, endptr);
2411  }
2412 
2413  static void strtof(double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
2414  {
2415  f = std::strtod(str, endptr);
2416  }
2417 
2418  static void strtof(long double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
2419  {
2420  f = std::strtold(str, endptr);
2421  }
2422 
2463  token_type scan_number()
2464  {
2465  // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
2466  reset();
2467 
2468  // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
2469  // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
2470  token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
2471 
2472  // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
2473  switch (current) {
2474  case '-': {
2475  add(current);
2476  goto scan_number_minus;
2477  }
2478 
2479  case '0': {
2480  add(current);
2481  goto scan_number_zero;
2482  }
2483 
2484  case '1':
2485  case '2':
2486  case '3':
2487  case '4':
2488  case '5':
2489  case '6':
2490  case '7':
2491  case '8':
2492  case '9': {
2493  add(current);
2494  goto scan_number_any1;
2495  }
2496 
2497  default: {
2498  // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
2499  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
2500  }
2501  }
2502 
2503  scan_number_minus:
2504  // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
2505  number_type = token_type::value_integer;
2506  switch (get()) {
2507  case '0': {
2508  add(current);
2509  goto scan_number_zero;
2510  }
2511 
2512  case '1':
2513  case '2':
2514  case '3':
2515  case '4':
2516  case '5':
2517  case '6':
2518  case '7':
2519  case '8':
2520  case '9': {
2521  add(current);
2522  goto scan_number_any1;
2523  }
2524 
2525  default: {
2526  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
2527  return token_type::parse_error;
2528  }
2529  }
2530 
2531  scan_number_zero:
2532  // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
2533  switch (get()) {
2534  case '.': {
2535  add(decimal_point_char);
2536  goto scan_number_decimal1;
2537  }
2538 
2539  case 'e':
2540  case 'E': {
2541  add(current);
2542  goto scan_number_exponent;
2543  }
2544 
2545  default:
2546  goto scan_number_done;
2547  }
2548 
2549  scan_number_any1:
2550  // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
2551  switch (get()) {
2552  case '0':
2553  case '1':
2554  case '2':
2555  case '3':
2556  case '4':
2557  case '5':
2558  case '6':
2559  case '7':
2560  case '8':
2561  case '9': {
2562  add(current);
2563  goto scan_number_any1;
2564  }
2565 
2566  case '.': {
2567  add(decimal_point_char);
2568  goto scan_number_decimal1;
2569  }
2570 
2571  case 'e':
2572  case 'E': {
2573  add(current);
2574  goto scan_number_exponent;
2575  }
2576 
2577  default:
2578  goto scan_number_done;
2579  }
2580 
2581  scan_number_decimal1:
2582  // state: we just parsed a decimal point
2583  number_type = token_type::value_float;
2584  switch (get()) {
2585  case '0':
2586  case '1':
2587  case '2':
2588  case '3':
2589  case '4':
2590  case '5':
2591  case '6':
2592  case '7':
2593  case '8':
2594  case '9': {
2595  add(current);
2596  goto scan_number_decimal2;
2597  }
2598 
2599  default: {
2600  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
2601  return token_type::parse_error;
2602  }
2603  }
2604 
2605  scan_number_decimal2:
2606  // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
2607  switch (get()) {
2608  case '0':
2609  case '1':
2610  case '2':
2611  case '3':
2612  case '4':
2613  case '5':
2614  case '6':
2615  case '7':
2616  case '8':
2617  case '9': {
2618  add(current);
2619  goto scan_number_decimal2;
2620  }
2621 
2622  case 'e':
2623  case 'E': {
2624  add(current);
2625  goto scan_number_exponent;
2626  }
2627 
2628  default:
2629  goto scan_number_done;
2630  }
2631 
2632  scan_number_exponent:
2633  // we just parsed an exponent
2634  number_type = token_type::value_float;
2635  switch (get()) {
2636  case '+':
2637  case '-': {
2638  add(current);
2639  goto scan_number_sign;
2640  }
2641 
2642  case '0':
2643  case '1':
2644  case '2':
2645  case '3':
2646  case '4':
2647  case '5':
2648  case '6':
2649  case '7':
2650  case '8':
2651  case '9': {
2652  add(current);
2653  goto scan_number_any2;
2654  }
2655 
2656  default: {
2657  error_message =
2658  "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
2659  return token_type::parse_error;
2660  }
2661  }
2662 
2663  scan_number_sign:
2664  // we just parsed an exponent sign
2665  switch (get()) {
2666  case '0':
2667  case '1':
2668  case '2':
2669  case '3':
2670  case '4':
2671  case '5':
2672  case '6':
2673  case '7':
2674  case '8':
2675  case '9': {
2676  add(current);
2677  goto scan_number_any2;
2678  }
2679 
2680  default: {
2681  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
2682  return token_type::parse_error;
2683  }
2684  }
2685 
2686  scan_number_any2:
2687  // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
2688  switch (get()) {
2689  case '0':
2690  case '1':
2691  case '2':
2692  case '3':
2693  case '4':
2694  case '5':
2695  case '6':
2696  case '7':
2697  case '8':
2698  case '9': {
2699  add(current);
2700  goto scan_number_any2;
2701  }
2702 
2703  default:
2704  goto scan_number_done;
2705  }
2706 
2707  scan_number_done:
2708  // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
2709  // we are done scanning a number)
2710  unget();
2711 
2712  char* endptr = nullptr;
2713  errno = 0;
2714 
2715  // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
2716  if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned) {
2717  const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
2718 
2719  // we checked the number format before
2720  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
2721 
2722  if (errno == 0) {
2723  value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
2724  if (value_unsigned == x) {
2725  return token_type::value_unsigned;
2726  }
2727  }
2728  } else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer) {
2729  const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
2730 
2731  // we checked the number format before
2732  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
2733 
2734  if (errno == 0) {
2735  value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
2736  if (value_integer == x) {
2737  return token_type::value_integer;
2738  }
2739  }
2740  }
2741 
2742  // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
2743  // integer conversion above failed
2744  strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
2745 
2746  // we checked the number format before
2747  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
2748 
2749  return token_type::value_float;
2750  }
2751 
2757  token_type scan_literal(const char* literal_text, const std::size_t length,
2758  token_type return_type)
2759  {
2760  assert(current == literal_text[0]);
2761  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i) {
2762  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get() != literal_text[i])) {
2763  error_message = "invalid literal";
2764  return token_type::parse_error;
2765  }
2766  }
2767  return return_type;
2768  }

2775  void reset() noexcept
2776  {
2777  token_buffer.clear();
2778  token_string.clear();
2779  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
2780  }
2781 
2782  /*
2783  @brief get next character from the input
2784 
2785  This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
2786  not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
2787  `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
2788  for use in error messages.
2789 
2790  @return character read from the input
2791  */
2792  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get()
2793  {
2794  ++chars_read;
2795  current = ia->get_character();
2796  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
2797  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
2798  }
2799  return current;
2800  }
2801 
2803  void unget()
2804  {
2805  --chars_read;
2806  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
2807  ia->unget_character();
2808  assert(token_string.size() != 0);
2809  token_string.pop_back();
2810  }
2811  }
2812 
2814  void add(int c)
2815  {
2816  token_buffer.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(c));
2817  }

2861  std::string get_token_string() const
2862  {
2863  // escape control characters
2864  std::string result;
2865  for (const auto c : token_string) {
2866  if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1F') {
2867  // escape control characters
2868  std::stringstream ss;
2869  ss << "<U+" << std::setw(4) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0')
2870  << std::hex << static_cast<int>(c) << ">";
2871  result += ss.str();
2872  } else {
2873  // add character as is
2874  result.push_back(c);
2875  }
2876  }
2877 
2878  return result;
2879  }

2883  {
2884  return error_message;

2888  // actual scanner
2890 
2891  token_type scan()
2892  {
2893  // read next character and ignore whitespace
2894  do {
2895  get();
2896  } while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
2897 
2898  switch (current) {
2899  // structural characters
2900  case '[':
2901  return token_type::begin_array;
2902  case ']':
2903  return token_type::end_array;
2904  case '{':
2905  return token_type::begin_object;
2906  case '}':
2907  return token_type::end_object;
2908  case ':':
2909  return token_type::name_separator;
2910  case ',':
2911  return token_type::value_separator;
2912 
2913  // literals
2914  case 't':
2915  return scan_literal("true", 4, token_type::literal_true);
2916  case 'f':
2917  return scan_literal("false", 5, token_type::literal_false);
2918  case 'n':
2919  return scan_literal("null", 4, token_type::literal_null);
2920 
2921  // string
2922  case '\"':
2923  return scan_string();
2924 
2925  // number
2926  case '-':
2927  case '0':
2928  case '1':
2929  case '2':
2930  case '3':
2931  case '4':
2932  case '5':
2933  case '6':
2934  case '7':
2935  case '8':
2936  case '9':
2937  return scan_number();
2938 
2939  // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
2940  // string literals)
2941  case '\0':
2942  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
2943  return token_type::end_of_input;
2944 
2945  // error
2946  default:
2947  error_message = "invalid literal";
2948  return token_type::parse_error;
2949  }
2950  }
2951 
2952  private:
2954  detail::input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
2955 
2957  std::char_traits<char>::int_type current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2958 
2960  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
2961 
2963  std::vector<char> token_string{};
2964 
2966  string_t token_buffer{};
2967 
2969  const char* error_message = "";
2970 
2971  // number values
2972  number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
2973  number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
2974  number_float_t value_float = 0;
2975 
2977  const char decimal_point_char = '.';
2978 };

3008 
3014 template <typename BasicJsonType>
3015 class parser
3016 {
3017  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3018  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3019  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3020  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3021  using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType>;
3022  using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
3023 
3024  public:
3025  enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t {
3027  object_start,
3029  object_end,
3031  array_start,
3033  array_end,
3035  key,
3037  value
3038  };
3039 
3040  using parser_callback_t =
3041  std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType& parsed)>;
3042 
3044  explicit parser(detail::input_adapter_t adapter,
3045  const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr,
3046  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
3047  : callback(cb), m_lexer(adapter), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
3048  {
3049  }
3050 
3061  void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result)
3062  {
3063  // read first token
3064  get_token();
3065 
3066  parse_internal(true, result);
3067  result.assert_invariant();
3068 
3069  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
3070  if (strict) {
3071  get_token();
3072  expect(token_type::end_of_input);
3073  }
3074 
3075  // in case of an error, return discarded value
3076  if (errored) {
3077  result = value_t::discarded;
3078  return;
3079  }
3080 
3081  // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
3082  // function
3083  if (result.is_discarded()) {
3084  result = nullptr;
3085  }
3086  }
3087 
3094  bool accept(const bool strict = true)
3095  {
3096  // read first token
3097  get_token();
3098 
3099  if (not accept_internal()) {
3100  return false;
3101  }
3102 
3103  // strict => last token must be EOF
3104  return not strict or (get_token() == token_type::end_of_input);
3105  }
3106 
3107  private:
3114  void parse_internal(bool keep, BasicJsonType& result)
3115  {
3116  // never parse after a parse error was detected
3117  assert(not errored);
3118 
3119  // start with a discarded value
3120  if (not result.is_discarded()) {
3121  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3122  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3123  }
3124 
3125  switch (last_token) {
3126  case token_type::begin_object: {
3127  if (keep) {
3128  if (callback) {
3129  keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::object_start, result);
3130  }
3131 
3132  if (not callback or keep) {
3133  // explicitly set result to object to cope with {}
3134  result.m_type = value_t::object;
3135  result.m_value = value_t::object;
3136  }
3137  }
3138 
3139  // read next token
3140  get_token();
3141 
3142  // closing } -> we are done
3143  if (last_token == token_type::end_object) {
3144  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
3145  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3146  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3147  }
3148  break;
3149  }
3150 
3151  // parse values
3152  string_t key;
3153  BasicJsonType value;
3154  while (true) {
3155  // store key
3156  if (not expect(token_type::value_string)) {
3157  return;
3158  }
3159  key = m_lexer.move_string();
3160 
3161  bool keep_tag = false;
3162  if (keep) {
3163  if (callback) {
3164  BasicJsonType k(key);
3165  keep_tag = callback(depth, parse_event_t::key, k);
3166  } else {
3167  keep_tag = true;
3168  }
3169  }
3170 
3171  // parse separator (:)
3172  get_token();
3173  if (not expect(token_type::name_separator)) {
3174  return;
3175  }
3176 
3177  // parse and add value
3178  get_token();
3179  value.m_value.destroy(value.m_type);
3180  value.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3181  parse_internal(keep, value);
3182 
3183  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(errored)) {
3184  return;
3185  }
3186 
3187  if (keep and keep_tag and not value.is_discarded()) {
3188  result.m_value.object->emplace(std::move(key), std::move(value));
3189  }
3190 
3191  // comma -> next value
3192  get_token();
3193  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3194  get_token();
3195  continue;
3196  }
3197 
3198  // closing }
3199  if (not expect(token_type::end_object)) {
3200  return;
3201  }
3202  break;
3203  }
3204 
3205  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
3206  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3207  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3208  }
3209  break;
3210  }
3211 
3212  case token_type::begin_array: {
3213  if (keep) {
3214  if (callback) {
3215  keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::array_start, result);
3216  }
3217 
3218  if (not callback or keep) {
3219  // explicitly set result to array to cope with []
3220  result.m_type = value_t::array;
3221  result.m_value = value_t::array;
3222  }
3223  }
3224 
3225  // read next token
3226  get_token();
3227 
3228  // closing ] -> we are done
3229  if (last_token == token_type::end_array) {
3230  if (callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
3231  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3232  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3233  }
3234  break;
3235  }
3236 
3237  // parse values
3238  BasicJsonType value;
3239  while (true) {
3240  // parse value
3241  value.m_value.destroy(value.m_type);
3242  value.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3243  parse_internal(keep, value);
3244 
3245  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(errored)) {
3246  return;
3247  }
3248 
3249  if (keep and not value.is_discarded()) {
3250  result.m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
3251  }
3252 
3253  // comma -> next value
3254  get_token();
3255  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3256  get_token();
3257  continue;
3258  }
3259 
3260  // closing ]
3261  if (not expect(token_type::end_array)) {
3262  return;
3263  }
3264  break;
3265  }
3266 
3267  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
3268  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3269  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3270  }
3271  break;
3272  }
3273 
3274  case token_type::literal_null: {
3275  result.m_type = value_t::null;
3276  break;
3277  }
3278 
3279  case token_type::value_string: {
3280  result.m_type = value_t::string;
3281  result.m_value = m_lexer.move_string();
3282  break;
3283  }
3284 
3285  case token_type::literal_true: {
3286  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
3287  result.m_value = true;
3288  break;
3289  }
3290 
3291  case token_type::literal_false: {
3292  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
3293  result.m_value = false;
3294  break;
3295  }
3296 
3297  case token_type::value_unsigned: {
3298  result.m_type = value_t::number_unsigned;
3299  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_unsigned();
3300  break;
3301  }
3302 
3303  case token_type::value_integer: {
3304  result.m_type = value_t::number_integer;
3305  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_integer();
3306  break;
3307  }
3308 
3309  case token_type::value_float: {
3310  result.m_type = value_t::number_float;
3311  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_float();
3312 
3313  // throw in case of infinity or NAN
3314  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(result.m_value.number_float))) {
3315  if (allow_exceptions) {
3316  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" +
3317  m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
3318  }
3319  expect(token_type::uninitialized);
3320  }
3321  break;
3322  }
3323 
3324  case token_type::parse_error: {
3325  // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
3326  if (not expect(token_type::uninitialized)) {
3327  return;
3328  }
3329  break; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3330  }
3331 
3332  default: {
3333  // the last token was unexpected; we expected a value
3334  if (not expect(token_type::literal_or_value)) {
3335  return;
3336  }
3337  break; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3338  }
3339  }
3340 
3341  if (keep and callback and not callback(depth, parse_event_t::value, result)) {
3342  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3343  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3344  }
3345  }
3346 
3357  bool accept_internal()
3358  {
3359  switch (last_token) {
3360  case token_type::begin_object: {
3361  // read next token
3362  get_token();
3363 
3364  // closing } -> we are done
3365  if (last_token == token_type::end_object) {
3366  return true;
3367  }
3368 
3369  // parse values
3370  while (true) {
3371  // parse key
3372  if (last_token != token_type::value_string) {
3373  return false;
3374  }
3375 
3376  // parse separator (:)
3377  get_token();
3378  if (last_token != token_type::name_separator) {
3379  return false;
3380  }
3381 
3382  // parse value
3383  get_token();
3384  if (not accept_internal()) {
3385  return false;
3386  }
3387 
3388  // comma -> next value
3389  get_token();
3390  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3391  get_token();
3392  continue;
3393  }
3394 
3395  // closing }
3396  return (last_token == token_type::end_object);
3397  }
3398  }
3399 
3400  case token_type::begin_array: {
3401  // read next token
3402  get_token();
3403 
3404  // closing ] -> we are done
3405  if (last_token == token_type::end_array) {
3406  return true;
3407  }
3408 
3409  // parse values
3410  while (true) {
3411  // parse value
3412  if (not accept_internal()) {
3413  return false;
3414  }
3415 
3416  // comma -> next value
3417  get_token();
3418  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3419  get_token();
3420  continue;
3421  }
3422 
3423  // closing ]
3424  return (last_token == token_type::end_array);
3425  }
3426  }
3427 
3428  case token_type::value_float: {
3429  // reject infinity or NAN
3430  return std::isfinite(m_lexer.get_number_float());
3431  }
3432 
3433  case token_type::literal_false:
3434  case token_type::literal_null:
3435  case token_type::literal_true:
3436  case token_type::value_integer:
3437  case token_type::value_string:
3438  case token_type::value_unsigned:
3439  return true;
3440 
3441  default: // the last token was unexpected
3442  return false;
3443  }
3444  }
3445 
3447  token_type get_token()
3448  {
3449  return (last_token = m_lexer.scan());
3450  }
3451 
3455  bool expect(token_type t)
3456  {
3457  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(t != last_token)) {
3458  errored = true;
3459  expected = t;
3460  if (allow_exceptions) {
3461  throw_exception();
3462  } else {
3463  return false;
3464  }
3465  }
3466 
3467  return true;
3468  }
3469 
3470  [[noreturn]] void throw_exception() const
3471  {
3472  std::string error_msg = "syntax error - ";
3473  if (last_token == token_type::parse_error) {
3474  error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" +
3475  m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
3476  } else {
3477  error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
3478  }
3479 
3480  if (expected != token_type::uninitialized) {
3481  error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
3482  }
3483 
3484  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), error_msg));
3485  }
3486 
3487  private:
3489  int depth = 0;
3491  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
3493  token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
3495  lexer_t m_lexer;
3497  bool errored = false;
3499  token_type expected = token_type::uninitialized;
3501  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
3502 };
3503 } // namespace detail
3504 } // namespace nlohmann
3505 
3506 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
3507 
3508 #include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
3509 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
3510 
3511 namespace nlohmann
3512 {
3513 namespace detail
3514 {
3515 /*
3516 @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
3517 
3518 This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
3519 string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
3520 to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
3521 a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
3522 end_value (`1`) models past the end.
3523 */
3524 class primitive_iterator_t
3525 {
3526  private:
3527  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
3528  static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
3529  static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
3530 
3532  difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
3533 
3534  public:
3535  constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept
3536  {
3537  return m_it;
3538  }
3539 
3541  void set_begin() noexcept
3542  {
3543  m_it = begin_value;
3544  }
3545 
3547  void set_end() noexcept
3548  {
3549  m_it = end_value;
3550  }
3551 
3553  constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
3554  {
3555  return m_it == begin_value;
3556  }
3557 
3559  constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
3560  {
3561  return m_it == end_value;
3562  }
3563 
3564  friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
3565  {
3566  return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
3567  }
3568 
3569  friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
3570  {
3571  return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
3572  }
3573 
3574  primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept
3575  {
3576  auto result = *this;
3577  result += n;
3578  return result;
3579  }
3580 
3581  friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
3582  {
3583  return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
3584  }
3585 
3586  primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept
3587  {
3588  ++m_it;
3589  return *this;
3590  }
3591 
3592  primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int) noexcept
3593  {
3594  auto result = *this;
3595  m_it++;
3596  return result;
3597  }
3598 
3599  primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept
3600  {
3601  --m_it;
3602  return *this;
3603  }
3604 
3605  primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int) noexcept
3606  {
3607  auto result = *this;
3608  m_it--;
3609  return result;
3610  }
3611 
3612  primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
3613  {
3614  m_it += n;
3615  return *this;
3616  }
3617 
3618  primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
3619  {
3620  m_it -= n;
3621  return *this;
3622  }
3623 };
3624 } // namespace detail
3625 } // namespace nlohmann

3633 namespace detail

3642 struct internal_iterator {
3644  typename BasicJsonType::object_t::iterator object_iterator{};
3646  typename BasicJsonType::array_t::iterator array_iterator{};
3648  primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator{};
3649 };

3675 // forward declare, to be able to friend it later on
3676 template <typename IteratorType>
3677 class iteration_proxy;
3678 
3699 template <typename BasicJsonType>
3700 class iter_impl
3701 {
3703  friend iter_impl<typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type, const BasicJsonType>::type>;
3704  friend BasicJsonType;
3705  friend iteration_proxy<iter_impl>;
3706 
3707  using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
3708  using array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
3709  // make sure BasicJsonType is basic_json or const basic_json
3710  static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
3711  "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
3712 
3713  public:
3719  using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
3720 
3722  using value_type = typename BasicJsonType::value_type;
3724  using difference_type = typename BasicJsonType::difference_type;
3726  using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
3727  typename BasicJsonType::const_pointer,
3728  typename BasicJsonType::pointer>::type;
3730  using reference =
3731  typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
3732  typename BasicJsonType::const_reference,
3733  typename BasicJsonType::reference>::type;
3734 
3736  iter_impl() = default;
3737 
3744  explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object)
3745  {
3746  assert(m_object != nullptr);
3747 
3748  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3749  case value_t::object: {
3750  m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
3751  break;
3752  }
3753 
3754  case value_t::array: {
3755  m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
3756  break;
3757  }
3758 
3759  default: {
3760  m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
3761  break;
3762  }
3763  }
3764  }
3765 
3780  iter_impl(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
3781  : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it) {}
3782 
3789  iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
3790  {
3791  m_object = other.m_object;
3792  m_it = other.m_it;
3793  return *this;
3794  }
3795 
3796  private:
3801  void set_begin() noexcept
3802  {
3803  assert(m_object != nullptr);
3804 
3805  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3806  case value_t::object: {
3807  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
3808  break;
3809  }
3810 
3811  case value_t::array: {
3812  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
3813  break;
3814  }
3815 
3816  case value_t::null: {
3817  // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
3818  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
3819  break;
3820  }
3821 
3822  default: {
3823  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
3824  break;
3825  }
3826  }
3827  }
3828 
3833  void set_end() noexcept
3834  {
3835  assert(m_object != nullptr);
3836 
3837  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3838  case value_t::object: {
3839  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
3840  break;
3841  }
3842 
3843  case value_t::array: {
3844  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
3845  break;
3846  }
3847 
3848  default: {
3849  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
3850  break;
3851  }
3852  }
3853  }
3854 
3855  public:
3860  reference operator*() const
3861  {
3862  assert(m_object != nullptr);
3863 
3864  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3865  case value_t::object: {
3866  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
3867  return m_it.object_iterator->second;
3868  }
3869 
3870  case value_t::array: {
3871  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
3872  return *m_it.array_iterator;
3873  }
3874 
3875  case value_t::null:
3876  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
3877 
3878  default: {
3879  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())) {
3880  return *m_object;
3881  }
3882 
3883  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
3884  }
3885  }
3886  }
3887 
3892  pointer operator->() const
3893  {
3894  assert(m_object != nullptr);
3895 
3896  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3897  case value_t::object: {
3898  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
3899  return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
3900  }
3901 
3902  case value_t::array: {
3903  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
3904  return &*m_it.array_iterator;
3905  }
3906 
3907  default: {
3908  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())) {
3909  return m_object;
3910  }
3911 
3912  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
3913  }
3914  }
3915  }
3916 
3921  iter_impl const operator++(int)
3922  {
3923  auto result = *this;
3924  ++(*this);
3925  return result;
3926  }
3927 
3932  iter_impl& operator++()
3933  {
3934  assert(m_object != nullptr);
3935 
3936  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3937  case value_t::object: {
3938  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, 1);
3939  break;
3940  }
3941 
3942  case value_t::array: {
3943  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
3944  break;
3945  }
3946 
3947  default: {
3948  ++m_it.primitive_iterator;
3949  break;
3950  }
3951  }
3952 
3953  return *this;
3954  }

3961  {
3962  auto result = *this;
3963  --(*this);
3964  return result;
3965  }
3966 
3971  iter_impl& operator--()
3972  {
3973  assert(m_object != nullptr);
3974 
3975  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3976  case value_t::object: {
3977  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
3978  break;
3979  }
3980 
3981  case value_t::array: {
3982  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
3983  break;
3984  }
3985 
3986  default: {
3987  --m_it.primitive_iterator;
3988  break;
3989  }
3990  }
3991 
3992  return *this;
3993  }
3994 
3999  bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const
4000  {
4001  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
4002  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object)) {
4003  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
4004  }
4005 
4006  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4007 
4008  switch (m_object->m_type) {
4009  case value_t::object:
4010  return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
4011 
4012  case value_t::array:
4013  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
4014 
4015  default:
4016  return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
4017  }
4018  }
4019 
4024  bool operator!=(const iter_impl& other) const
4025  {
4026  return not operator==(other);
4027  }
4028 
4033  bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const
4034  {
4035  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
4036  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object)) {
4037  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
4038  }
4039 
4040  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4041 
4042  switch (m_object->m_type) {
4043  case value_t::object:
4044  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(213, "cannot compare order of object iterators"));
4045 
4046  case value_t::array:
4047  return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
4048 
4049  default:
4050  return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
4051  }
4052  }
4053 
4058  bool operator<=(const iter_impl& other) const
4059  {
4060  return not other.operator<(*this);
4061  }
4062 
4067  bool operator>(const iter_impl& other) const
4068  {

4070  }
4071 
4076  bool operator>=(const iter_impl& other) const
4077  {
4078  return not operator<(other);
4079  }
4080 
4085  iter_impl& operator+=(difference_type i)
4086  {
4087  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4088 
4089  switch (m_object->m_type) {
4090  case value_t::object:
4091  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
4092 
4093  case value_t::array: {
4094  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, i);
4095  break;
4096  }
4097 
4098  default: {
4099  m_it.primitive_iterator += i;
4100  break;
4101  }
4102  }
4103 
4104  return *this;
4105  }
4106 
4111  iter_impl& operator-=(difference_type i)
4112  {
4113  return operator+=(-i);
4114  }
4115 
4120  iter_impl operator+(difference_type i) const
4121  {
4122  auto result = *this;
4123  result += i;
4124  return result;
4125  }
4126 
4131  friend iter_impl operator+(difference_type i, const iter_impl& it)
4132  {
4133  auto result = it;
4134  result += i;
4135  return result;
4136  }
4137 
4142  iter_impl operator-(difference_type i) const
4143  {
4144  auto result = *this;
4145  result -= i;
4146  return result;
4147  }
4148 
4153  difference_type operator-(const iter_impl& other) const
4154  {
4155  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4156 
4157  switch (m_object->m_type) {
4158  case value_t::object:
4159  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
4160 
4161  case value_t::array:
4162  return m_it.array_iterator - other.m_it.array_iterator;
4163 
4164  default:
4165  return m_it.primitive_iterator - other.m_it.primitive_iterator;
4166  }
4167  }
4168 
4173  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
4174  {
4175  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4176 
4177  switch (m_object->m_type) {
4178  case value_t::object:
4179  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(208, "cannot use operator[] for object iterators"));
4180 
4181  case value_t::array:
4182  return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
4183 
4184  case value_t::null:
4185  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
4186 
4187  default: {
4188  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.get_value() == -n)) {
4189  return *m_object;
4190  }
4191 
4192  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
4193  }
4194  }
4195  }
4196 
4201  typename object_t::key_type key() const
4202  {
4203  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4204 
4205  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_object->is_object())) {
4206  return m_it.object_iterator->first;
4207  }
4208 
4209  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(207, "cannot use key() for non-object iterators"));
4210  }
4211 
4216  reference value() const
4217  {
4218  return operator*();
4219  }
4220 
4221  private:
4223  pointer m_object = nullptr;
4225  internal_iterator<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type> m_it;
4226 };
4227 } // namespace detail
4228 } // namespace nlohmann

4239 namespace detail
