4242 template <typename IteratorType>
4243 class iteration_proxy
4244 {
4245  private:
4247  class iteration_proxy_internal
4248  {
4249  private:
4251  IteratorType anchor;
4253  std::size_t array_index = 0;
4254 
4255  public:
4256  explicit iteration_proxy_internal(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {}
4257 
4259  iteration_proxy_internal& operator*()
4260  {
4261  return *this;
4262  }
4263 
4265  iteration_proxy_internal& operator++()
4266  {
4267  ++anchor;
4268  ++array_index;
4269 
4270  return *this;
4271  }
4272 
4274  bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_internal& o) const noexcept
4275  {
4276  return anchor != o.anchor;
4277  }
4278 
4280  std::string key() const
4281  {
4282  assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
4283 
4284  switch (anchor.m_object->type()) {
4285  // use integer array index as key
4286  case value_t::array:
4287  return std::to_string(array_index);
4288 
4289  // use key from the object
4290  case value_t::object:
4291  return anchor.key();
4292 
4293  // use an empty key for all primitive types
4294  default:
4295  return "";
4296  }
4297  }
4298 
4300  typename IteratorType::reference value() const
4301  {
4302  return anchor.value();
4303  }
4304  };
4305 
4307  typename IteratorType::reference container;
4308 
4309  public:
4311  explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept
4312  : container(cont) {}
4313 
4315  iteration_proxy_internal begin() noexcept
4316  {
4317  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.begin());
4318  }
4319 
4321  iteration_proxy_internal end() noexcept
4322  {
4323  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.end());
4324  }
4325 };
4326 } // namespace detail
4327 } // namespace nlohmann

4369  using reference = typename Base::reference;

4373  : base_iterator(it) {}
4374

4377

4380  {

4382  }
4383

4388  }
4389

4392  {

4394  }

4400  }
4401

4404  {

4406  }
4407

4412  }

4418  }

4437  }

4465 template <typename CharType>
4466 struct output_adapter_protocol {
4467  virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
4468  virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
4469  virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
4470 };
4471 
4473 template <typename CharType>
4474 using output_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<output_adapter_protocol<CharType>>;
4475 
4477 template <typename CharType>
4478 class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
4479 {
4480  public:
4481  explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) : v(vec) {}
4482 
4483  void write_character(CharType c) override
4484  {
4485  v.push_back(c);
4486  }
4487 
4488  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
4489  {
4490  std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
4491  }
4492 
4493  private:
4494  std::vector<CharType>& v;
4495 };
4496 
4498 template <typename CharType>
4499 class output_stream_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
4500 {
4501  public:
4502  explicit output_stream_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) : stream(s) {}
4503 
4504  void write_character(CharType c) override
4505  {
4506  stream.put(c);
4507  }
4508 
4509  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
4510  {
4511  stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
4512  }
4513 
4514  private:
4515  std::basic_ostream<CharType>& stream;
4516 };
4517 
4519 template <typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
4520 class output_string_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
4521 {
4522  public:
4523  explicit output_string_adapter(StringType& s) : str(s) {}
4524 
4525  void write_character(CharType c) override
4526  {
4527  str.push_back(c);
4528  }
4529 
4530  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
4531  {
4532  str.append(s, length);
4533  }
4534 
4535  private:
4536  StringType& str;
4537 };
4538 
4539 template <typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
4540 class output_adapter
4541 {
4542  public:
4543  output_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec)
4544  : oa(std::make_shared<output_vector_adapter<CharType>>(vec)) {}
4545 
4546  output_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s)
4547  : oa(std::make_shared<output_stream_adapter<CharType>>(s)) {}
4548 
4549  output_adapter(StringType& s)
4550  : oa(std::make_shared<output_string_adapter<CharType, StringType>>(s)) {}
4551 
4552  operator output_adapter_t<CharType>()
4553  {
4554  return oa;
4555  }
4556 
4557  private:
4558  output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
4559 };

4599 template <typename BasicJsonType>
4600 class binary_reader
4601 {
4602  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4603  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4604  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4605 
4606  public:
4612  explicit binary_reader(input_adapter_t adapter) : ia(std::move(adapter))
4613  {
4614  assert(ia);
4615  }
4616 
4627  BasicJsonType parse_cbor(const bool strict)
4628  {
4629  const auto res = parse_cbor_internal();
4630  if (strict) {
4631  get();
4632  expect_eof();
4633  }
4634  return res;
4635  }
4636 
4647  BasicJsonType parse_msgpack(const bool strict)
4648  {
4649  const auto res = parse_msgpack_internal();
4650  if (strict) {
4651  get();
4652  expect_eof();
4653  }
4654  return res;
4655  }

4676 
4684  static constexpr bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept
4685  {
4686  return (*reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1);
4687  }
4688 
4689  private:
4695  BasicJsonType parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char = true)
4696  {
4697  switch (get_char ? get() : current) {
4698  // EOF
4699  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
4700  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
4701 
4702  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
4703  case 0x00:
4704  case 0x01:
4705  case 0x02:
4706  case 0x03:
4707  case 0x04:
4708  case 0x05:
4709  case 0x06:
4710  case 0x07:
4711  case 0x08:
4712  case 0x09:
4713  case 0x0A:
4714  case 0x0B:
4715  case 0x0C:
4716  case 0x0D:
4717  case 0x0E:
4718  case 0x0F:
4719  case 0x10:
4720  case 0x11:
4721  case 0x12:
4722  case 0x13:
4723  case 0x14:
4724  case 0x15:
4725  case 0x16:
4726  case 0x17:
4727  return static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current);
4728 
4729  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
4730  return get_number<uint8_t>();
4731 
4732  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
4733  return get_number<uint16_t>();
4734 
4735  case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
4736  return get_number<uint32_t>();
4737 
4738  case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
4739  return get_number<uint64_t>();
4740 
4741  // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
4742  case 0x20:
4743  case 0x21:
4744  case 0x22:
4745  case 0x23:
4746  case 0x24:
4747  case 0x25:
4748  case 0x26:
4749  case 0x27:
4750  case 0x28:
4751  case 0x29:
4752  case 0x2A:
4753  case 0x2B:
4754  case 0x2C:
4755  case 0x2D:
4756  case 0x2E:
4757  case 0x2F:
4758  case 0x30:
4759  case 0x31:
4760  case 0x32:
4761  case 0x33:
4762  case 0x34:
4763  case 0x35:
4764  case 0x36:
4765  case 0x37:
4766  return static_cast<int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current);
4767 
4768  case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
4769  {
4770  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint8_t>();
4771  }
4772 
4773  case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
4774  {
4775  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint16_t>();
4776  }
4777 
4778  case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
4779  {
4780  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint32_t>();
4781  }
4782 
4783  case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
4784  {
4785  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) -
4786  static_cast<number_integer_t>(get_number<uint64_t>());
4787  }
4788 
4789  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
4790  case 0x60:
4791  case 0x61:
4792  case 0x62:
4793  case 0x63:
4794  case 0x64:
4795  case 0x65:
4796  case 0x66:
4797  case 0x67:
4798  case 0x68:
4799  case 0x69:
4800  case 0x6A:
4801  case 0x6B:
4802  case 0x6C:
4803  case 0x6D:
4804  case 0x6E:
4805  case 0x6F:
4806  case 0x70:
4807  case 0x71:
4808  case 0x72:
4809  case 0x73:
4810  case 0x74:
4811  case 0x75:
4812  case 0x76:
4813  case 0x77:
4814  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4815  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4816  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4817  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4818  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
4819  {
4820  return get_cbor_string();
4821  }
4822 
4823  // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
4824  case 0x80:
4825  case 0x81:
4826  case 0x82:
4827  case 0x83:
4828  case 0x84:
4829  case 0x85:
4830  case 0x86:
4831  case 0x87:
4832  case 0x88:
4833  case 0x89:
4834  case 0x8A:
4835  case 0x8B:
4836  case 0x8C:
4837  case 0x8D:
4838  case 0x8E:
4839  case 0x8F:
4840  case 0x90:
4841  case 0x91:
4842  case 0x92:
4843  case 0x93:
4844  case 0x94:
4845  case 0x95:
4846  case 0x96:
4847  case 0x97: {
4848  return get_cbor_array(current & 0x1F);
4849  }
4850 
4851  case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4852  {
4853  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint8_t>());
4854  }
4855 
4856  case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4857  {
4858  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint16_t>());
4859  }
4860 
4861  case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4862  {
4863  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint32_t>());
4864  }
4865 
4866  case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4867  {
4868  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint64_t>());
4869  }
4870 
4871  case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
4872  {
4873  BasicJsonType result = value_t::array;
4874  while (get() != 0xFF) {
4875  result.push_back(parse_cbor_internal(false));
4876  }
4877  return result;
4878  }
4879 
4880  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
4881  case 0xA0:
4882  case 0xA1:
4883  case 0xA2:
4884  case 0xA3:
4885  case 0xA4:
4886  case 0xA5:
4887  case 0xA6:
4888  case 0xA7:
4889  case 0xA8:
4890  case 0xA9:
4891  case 0xAA:
4892  case 0xAB:
4893  case 0xAC:
4894  case 0xAD:
4895  case 0xAE:
4896  case 0xAF:
4897  case 0xB0:
4898  case 0xB1:
4899  case 0xB2:
4900  case 0xB3:
4901  case 0xB4:
4902  case 0xB5:
4903  case 0xB6:
4904  case 0xB7: {
4905  return get_cbor_object(current & 0x1F);
4906  }
4907 
4908  case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4909  {
4910  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint8_t>());
4911  }
4912 
4913  case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4914  {
4915  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint16_t>());
4916  }
4917 
4918  case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4919  {
4920  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint32_t>());
4921  }
4922 
4923  case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4924  {
4925  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint64_t>());
4926  }
4927 
4928  case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
4929  {
4930  BasicJsonType result = value_t::object;
4931  while (get() != 0xFF) {
4932  auto key = get_cbor_string();
4933  result[key] = parse_cbor_internal();
4934  }
4935  return result;
4936  }
4937 
4938  case 0xF4: // false
4939  {
4940  return false;
4941  }
4942 
4943  case 0xF5: // true
4944  {
4945  return true;
4946  }
4947 
4948  case 0xF6: // null
4949  {
4950  return value_t::null;
4951  }
4952 
4953  case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
4954  {
4955  const int byte1 = get();
4956  unexpect_eof();
4957  const int byte2 = get();
4958  unexpect_eof();
4959 
4960  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
4961  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
4962  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
4963  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
4964  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
4965  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
4966  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
4967  // is shown in Fig. 3.
4968  const int half = (byte1 << 8) + byte2;
4969  const int exp = (half >> 10) & 0x1F;
4970  const int mant = half & 0x3FF;
4971  double val;
4972  if (exp == 0) {
4973  val = std::ldexp(mant, -24);
4974  } else if (exp != 31) {
4975  val = std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
4976  } else {
4977  val = (mant == 0) ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
4978  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4979  }
4980  return (half & 0x8000) != 0 ? -val : val;
4981  }
4982 
4983  case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
4984  {
4985  return get_number<float>();
4986  }
4987 
4988  case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
4989  {
4990  return get_number<double>();
4991  }
4992 
4993  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
4994  {
4995  std::stringstream ss;
4996  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
4997  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read, "error reading CBOR; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
4998  }
4999  }
5000  }

5360 
5361  /*
5362  @brief read a number from the input
5363 
5364  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
5365 
5366  @return number of type @a NumberType
5367 
5368  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
5369  bytes in CBOR and MessagePack are stored in network order (big
5370  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
5371 
5372  @throw parse_error.110 if input has less than `sizeof(NumberType)` bytes
5373  */
5374  template <typename NumberType>
5375  NumberType get_number()
5376  {
5377  // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
5378  std::array<uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
5379  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i) {
5380  get();
5381  unexpect_eof();
5382 
5383  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
5384  if (is_little_endian) {
5385  vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current);
5386  } else {
5387  vec[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5388  }
5389  }
5390 
5391  // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
5392  NumberType result;
5393  std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
5394  return result;
5395  }
5396 
5410  template <typename NumberType>
5411  string_t get_string(const NumberType len)
5412  {
5413  string_t result;
5414  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(result), len, [this]() {
5415  get();
5416  unexpect_eof();
5417  return static_cast<char>(current);
5418  });
5419  return result;
5420  }

5434  string_t get_cbor_string()
5435  {
5436  unexpect_eof();
5437 
5438  switch (current) {
5439  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
5440  case 0x60:
5441  case 0x61:
5442  case 0x62:
5443  case 0x63:
5444  case 0x64:
5445  case 0x65:
5446  case 0x66:
5447  case 0x67:
5448  case 0x68:
5449  case 0x69:
5450  case 0x6A:
5451  case 0x6B:
5452  case 0x6C:
5453  case 0x6D:
5454  case 0x6E:
5455  case 0x6F:
5456  case 0x70:
5457  case 0x71:
5458  case 0x72:
5459  case 0x73:
5460  case 0x74:
5461  case 0x75:
5462  case 0x76:
5463  case 0x77: {
5464  return get_string(current & 0x1F);
5465  }
5466 
5467  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5468  {
5469  return get_string(get_number<uint8_t>());
5470  }
5471 
5472  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5473  {
5474  return get_string(get_number<uint16_t>());
5475  }
5476 
5477  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5478  {
5479  return get_string(get_number<uint32_t>());
5480  }
5481 
5482  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5483  {
5484  return get_string(get_number<uint64_t>());
5485  }
5486 
5487  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
5488  {
5489  string_t result;
5490  while (get() != 0xFF) {
5491  result.append(get_cbor_string());
5492  }
5493  return result;
5494  }
5495 
5496  default: {
5497  std::stringstream ss;
5498  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5499  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a CBOR string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5500  }
5501  }
5502  }

5646  string_t get_ubjson_string(const bool get_char = true)
5647  {
5648  if (get_char) {
5649  get(); // TODO: may we ignore N here?
5650  }
5651 
5652  unexpect_eof();
5653 
5654  switch (current) {
5655  case 'U':
5656  return get_string(get_number<uint8_t>());
5657  case 'i':
5658  return get_string(get_number<int8_t>());
5659  case 'I':
5660  return get_string(get_number<int16_t>());
5661  case 'l':
5662  return get_string(get_number<int32_t>());
5663  case 'L':
5664  return get_string(get_number<int64_t>());
5665  default:
5666  std::stringstream ss;
5667  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5668  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
5669  "expected a UBJSON string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5670  }
5671  }
5672 
5681  std::pair<std::size_t, int> get_ubjson_size_type()
5682  {
5683  std::size_t sz = string_t::npos;
5684  int tc = 0;
5685 
5686  get_ignore_noop();
5687 
5688  if (current == '$') {
5689  tc = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
5690  unexpect_eof();
5691 
5692  get_ignore_noop();
5693  if (current != '#') {
5694  std::stringstream ss;
5695  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5696  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
5697  "expected '#' after UBJSON type information; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5698  }
5699  sz = parse_ubjson_internal();
5700  } else if (current == '#') {
5701  sz = parse_ubjson_internal();
5702  }
5703 
5704  return std::make_pair(sz, tc);
5705  }
5706 
5707  BasicJsonType get_ubjson_value(const int prefix)
5708  {
5709  switch (prefix) {
5710  case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): // EOF
5711  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
5712 
5713  case 'T': // true
5714  return true;
5715  case 'F': // false
5716  return false;
5717 
5718  case 'Z': // null
5719  return nullptr;
5720 
5721  case 'U':
5722  return get_number<uint8_t>();
5723  case 'i':
5724  return get_number<int8_t>();
5725  case 'I':
5726  return get_number<int16_t>();
5727  case 'l':
5728  return get_number<int32_t>();
5729  case 'L':
5730  return get_number<int64_t>();
5731  case 'd':
5732  return get_number<float>();
5733  case 'D':
5734  return get_number<double>();
5735 
5736  case 'C': // char
5737  {
5738  get();
5739  unexpect_eof();
5740  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current > 127)) {
5741  std::stringstream ss;
5742  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5743  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
5744  "byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5745  }
5746  return string_t(1, static_cast<char>(current));
5747  }
5748 
5749  case 'S': // string
5750  return get_ubjson_string();
5751 
5752  case '[': // array
5753  return get_ubjson_array();
5754 
5755  case '{': // object
5756  return get_ubjson_object();
5757 
5758  default: // anything else
5759  std::stringstream ss;
5760  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5761  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
5762  "error reading UBJSON; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5763  }
5764  }
5765 
5766  BasicJsonType get_ubjson_array()
5767  {
5768  BasicJsonType result = value_t::array;
5769  const auto size_and_type = get_ubjson_size_type();
5770 
5771  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos) {
5772  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(size_and_type.first > result.max_size())) {
5773  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
5774  "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(size_and_type.first)));
5775  }
5776 
5777  if (size_and_type.second != 0) {
5778  if (size_and_type.second != 'N') {
5779  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(*result.m_value.array),
5780  size_and_type.first, [this, size_and_type]() {
5781  return get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second);
5782  });
5783  }
5784  } else {
5785  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(*result.m_value.array),
5786  size_and_type.first, [this]() {
5787  return parse_ubjson_internal();
5788  });
5789  }
5790  } else {
5791  while (current != ']') {
5792  result.push_back(parse_ubjson_internal(false));
5793  get_ignore_noop();
5794  }
5795  }
5796 
5797  return result;
5798  }
5799 
5800  BasicJsonType get_ubjson_object()
5801  {
5802  BasicJsonType result = value_t::object;
5803  const auto size_and_type = get_ubjson_size_type();
5804 
5805  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos) {
5806  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(size_and_type.first > result.max_size())) {
5807  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
5808  "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(size_and_type.first)));
5809  }
5810 
5811  if (size_and_type.second != 0) {
5812  std::generate_n(std::inserter(*result.m_value.object,
5813  result.m_value.object->end()),
5814  size_and_type.first, [this, size_and_type]() {
5815  auto key = get_ubjson_string();
5816  auto val = get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second);
5817  return std::make_pair(std::move(key), std::move(val));
5818  });
5819  } else {
5820  std::generate_n(std::inserter(*result.m_value.object,
5821  result.m_value.object->end()),
5822  size_and_type.first, [this]() {
5823  auto key = get_ubjson_string();
5824  auto val = parse_ubjson_internal();
5825  return std::make_pair(std::move(key), std::move(val));
5826  });
5827  }
5828  } else {
5829  while (current != '}') {
5830  auto key = get_ubjson_string(false);
5831  result[std::move(key)] = parse_ubjson_internal();
5832  get_ignore_noop();
5833  }
5834  }
5835 
5836  return result;
5837  }
5838 
5843  void expect_eof() const
5844  {
5845  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
5846  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "expected end of input"));
5847  }
5848  }
5849 
5854  void unexpect_eof() const
5855  {
5856  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
5857  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
5858  }
5859  }
5860 
5861  private:
5863  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
5864 
5866  int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
5867 
5869  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
5870 
5872  const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
5873 };
5874 } // namespace detail
5875 } // namespace nlohmann

5881 #include <cstdint> // uint8_t, uint16_t, uint32_t, uint64_t
5882 #include <cstring> // memcpy
5883 #include <limits> // numeric_limits

5900 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CharType>
5901 class binary_writer
5902 {
5903  public:
5909  explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<CharType> adapter) : oa(adapter)
5910  {
5911  assert(oa);
5912  }
5913 
5917  void write_cbor(const BasicJsonType& j)
5918  {
5919  switch (j.type()) {
5920  case value_t::null: {
5921  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xF6));
5922  break;
5923  }
5924 
5925  case value_t::boolean: {
5926  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
5927  ? static_cast<CharType>(0xF5)
5928  : static_cast<CharType>(0xF4));
5929  break;
5930  }
5931 
5932  case value_t::number_integer: {
5933  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0) {
5934  // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
5935  // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
5936  // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
5937  if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17) {
5938  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
5939  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
5940  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x18));
5941  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
5942  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
5943  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x19));
5944  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
5945  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
5946  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1A));
5947  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
5948  } else {
5949  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1B));
5950  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
5951  }
5952  } else {
5953  // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
5954  // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
5955  const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
5956  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24) {
5957  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
5958  } else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
5959  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x38));
5960  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(positive_number));
5961  } else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
5962  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x39));
5963  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(positive_number));
5964  } else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
5965  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x3A));
5966  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(positive_number));
5967  } else {
5968  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x3B));
5969  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(positive_number));
5970  }
5971  }
5972  break;
5973  }
5974 
5975  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
5976  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17) {
5977  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
5978  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
5979  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x18));
5980  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
5981  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
5982  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x19));
5983  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
5984  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
5985  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1A));
5986  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
5987  } else {
5988  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1B));
5989  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
5990  }
5991  break;
5992  }
5993 
5994  case value_t::number_float: // Double-Precision Float
5995  {
5996  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xFB));
5997  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
5998  break;
5999  }
6000 
6001  case value_t::string: {
6002  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
6003  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6004  if (N <= 0x17) {
6005  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
6006  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6007  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x78));
6008  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6009  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6010  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x79));
6011  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6012  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6013  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x7A));
6014  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6015  }
6016  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6017  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)()) {
6018  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x7B));
6019  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
6020  }
6021  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6022 
6023  // step 2: write the string
6024  oa->write_characters(
6025  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
6026  j.m_value.string->size());
6027  break;
6028  }
6029 
6030  case value_t::array: {
6031  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
6032  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6033  if (N <= 0x17) {
6034  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
6035  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6036  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x98));
6037  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6038  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6039  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x99));
6040  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6041  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6042  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x9A));
6043  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6044  }
6045  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6046  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)()) {
6047  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x9B));
6048  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
6049  }
6050  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6051 
6052  // step 2: write each element
6053  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
6054  write_cbor(el);
6055  }
6056  break;
6057  }
6058 
6059  case value_t::object: {
6060  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
6061  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6062  if (N <= 0x17) {
6063  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xA0 + N));
6064  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6065  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xB8));
6066  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6067  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6068  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xB9));
6069  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6070  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6071  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xBA));
6072  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6073  }
6074  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6075  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)()) {
6076  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xBB));
6077  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
6078  }
6079  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6080 
6081  // step 2: write each element
6082  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
6083  write_cbor(el.first);
6084  write_cbor(el.second);
6085  }
6086  break;
6087  }
6088 
6089  default:
6090  break;
6091  }
6092  }
6093 
6097  void write_msgpack(const BasicJsonType& j)
6098  {
6099  switch (j.type()) {
6100  case value_t::null: // nil
6101  {
6102  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xC0));
6103  break;
6104  }
6105 
6106  case value_t::boolean: // true and false
6107  {
6108  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
6109  ? static_cast<CharType>(0xC3)
6110  : static_cast<CharType>(0xC2));
6111  break;
6112  }
6113 
6114  case value_t::number_integer: {
6115  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0) {
6116  // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
6117  // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used
6118  // the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
6119  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128) {
6120  // positive fixnum
6121  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6122  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6123  // uint 8
6124  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCC));
6125  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6126  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6127  // uint 16
6128  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCD));
6129  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6130  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6131  // uint 32
6132  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCE));
6133  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6134  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)()) {
6135  // uint 64
6136  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCF));
6137  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6138  }
6139  } else {
6140  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32) {
6141  // negative fixnum
6142  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6143  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min)() and
6144  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)()) {
6145  // int 8
6146  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD0));
6147  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6148  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min)() and
6149  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)()) {
6150  // int 16
6151  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD1));
6152  write_number(static_cast<int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6153  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min)() and
6154  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)()) {
6155  // int 32
6156  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD2));
6157  write_number(static_cast<int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6158  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)() and
6159  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)()) {
6160  // int 64
6161  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD3));
6162  write_number(static_cast<int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6163  }
6164  }
6165  break;
6166  }
6167 
6168  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
6169  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128) {
6170  // positive fixnum
6171  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6172  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6173  // uint 8
6174  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCC));
6175  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6176  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6177  // uint 16
6178  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCD));
6179  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6180  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6181  // uint 32
6182  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCE));
6183  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6184  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)()) {
6185  // uint 64
6186  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCF));
6187  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6188  }
6189  break;
6190  }
6191 
6192  case value_t::number_float: // float 64
6193  {
6194  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCB));
6195  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
6196  break;
6197  }
6198 
6199  case value_t::string: {
6200  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
6201  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6202  if (N <= 31) {
6203  // fixstr
6204  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xA0 | N));
6205  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6206  // str 8
6207  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD9));
6208  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6209  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6210  // str 16
6211  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDA));
6212  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6213  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6214  // str 32
6215  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDB));
6216  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6217  }
6218 
6219  // step 2: write the string
6220  oa->write_characters(
6221  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
6222  j.m_value.string->size());
6223  break;
6224  }
6225 
6226  case value_t::array: {
6227  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
6228  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6229  if (N <= 15) {
6230  // fixarray
6231  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
6232  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6233  // array 16
6234  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDC));
6235  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6236  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6237  // array 32
6238  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDD));
6239  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6240  }
6241 
6242  // step 2: write each element
6243  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
6244  write_msgpack(el);
6245  }
6246  break;
6247  }
6248 
6249  case value_t::object: {
6250  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
6251  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6252  if (N <= 15) {
6253  // fixmap
6254  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xF)));
6255  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)()) {
6256  // map 16
6257  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDE));
6258  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6259  } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)()) {
6260  // map 32
6261  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDF));
6262  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6263  }
6264 
6265  // step 2: write each element
6266  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
6267  write_msgpack(el.first);
6268  write_msgpack(el.second);
6269  }
6270  break;
6271  }
6272 
6273  default:
6274  break;
6275  }
6276  }
6277 
6284  void write_ubjson(const BasicJsonType& j, const bool use_count,
6285  const bool use_type, const bool add_prefix = true)
6286  {
6287  switch (j.type()) {
6288  case value_t::null: {
6289  if (add_prefix) {
6290  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('Z'));
6291  }
6292  break;
6293  }
6294 
6295  case value_t::boolean: {
6296  if (add_prefix)
6297  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
6298  ? static_cast<CharType>('T')
6299  : static_cast<CharType>('F'));
6300  break;
6301  }
6302 
6303  case value_t::number_integer: {
6304  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_integer, add_prefix);
6305  break;
6306  }
6307 
6308  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
6309  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_unsigned, add_prefix);
6310  break;
6311  }
6312 
6313  case value_t::number_float: {
6314  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_float, add_prefix);
6315  break;
6316  }
6317 
6318  case value_t::string: {
6319  if (add_prefix) {
6320  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('S'));
6321  }
6322  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.string->size(), true);
6323  oa->write_characters(
6324  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
6325  j.m_value.string->size());
6326  break;
6327  }
6328 
6329  case value_t::array: {
6330  if (add_prefix) {
6331  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('['));
6332  }
6333 
6334  bool prefix_required = true;
6335  if (use_type and not j.m_value.array->empty()) {
6336  assert(use_count);
6337  const char first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
6338  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin() + 1, j.end(),
6339  [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType& v) {
6340  return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
6341  });
6342 
6343  if (same_prefix) {
6344  prefix_required = false;
6345  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('$'));
6346  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(first_prefix));
6347  }
6348  }
6349 
6350  if (use_count) {
6351  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('#'));
6352  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.array->size(), true);
6353  }
6354 
6355  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
6356  write_ubjson(el, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
6357  }
6358 
6359  if (not use_count) {
6360  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(']'));
6361  }
6362 
6363  break;
6364  }
6365 
6366  case value_t::object: {
6367  if (add_prefix) {
6368  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('{'));
6369  }
6370 
6371  bool prefix_required = true;
6372  if (use_type and not j.m_value.object->empty()) {
6373  assert(use_count);
6374  const char first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
6375  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin(), j.end(),
6376  [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType& v) {
6377  return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
6378  });
6379 
6380  if (same_prefix) {
6381  prefix_required = false;
6382  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('$'));
6383  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(first_prefix));
6384  }
6385  }
6386 
6387  if (use_count) {
6388  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('#'));
6389  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.object->size(), true);
6390  }
6391 
6392  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
6393  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(el.first.size(), true);
6394  oa->write_characters(
6395  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(el.first.c_str()),
6396  el.first.size());
6397  write_ubjson(el.second, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
6398  }
6399 
6400  if (not use_count) {
6401  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('}'));
6402  }
6403 
6404  break;
6405  }
6406 
6407  default:
6408  break;
6409  }
6410  }
6411 
6412  private:
6413  /*
6414  @brief write a number to output input
6415 
6416  @param[in] n number of type @a NumberType
6417  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
6418 
6419  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because bytes
6420  in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order (big
6421  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
6422  */
6423  template <typename NumberType>
6424  void write_number(const NumberType n)
6425  {
6426  // step 1: write number to array of length NumberType
6427  std::array<CharType, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
6428  std::memcpy(vec.data(), &n, sizeof(NumberType));
6429 
6430  // step 2: write array to output (with possible reordering)
6431  if (is_little_endian) {
6432  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
6433  std::reverse(vec.begin(), vec.end());
6434  }
6435 
6436  oa->write_characters(vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
6437  }
6438 
6439  // UBJSON: write number (floating point)
6440  template <typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
6441  std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
6442  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
6443  const bool add_prefix)
6444  {
6445  if (add_prefix) {
6446  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('D')); // float64
6447  }
6448  write_number(n);
6449  }
6450 
6451  // UBJSON: write number (unsigned integer)
6452  template <typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
6453  std::is_unsigned<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
6454  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
6455  const bool add_prefix)
6456  {
6457  if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)())) {
6458  if (add_prefix) {
6459  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('i')); // int8
6460  }
6461  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(n));
6462  } else if (n <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6463  if (add_prefix) {
6464  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('U')); // uint8
6465  }
6466  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(n));
6467  } else if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)())) {
6468  if (add_prefix) {
6469  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('I')); // int16
6470  }
6471  write_number(static_cast<int16_t>(n));
6472  } else if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)())) {
6473  if (add_prefix) {
6474  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('l')); // int32
6475  }
6476  write_number(static_cast<int32_t>(n));
6477  } else if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)())) {
6478  if (add_prefix) {
6479  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('L')); // int64
6480  }
6481  write_number(static_cast<int64_t>(n));
6482  } else {
6483  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "number overflow serializing " + std::to_string(n)));
6484  }
6485  }
6486 
6487  // UBJSON: write number (signed integer)
6488  template <typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
6489  std::is_signed<NumberType>::value and
6490  not std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value,
6491  int>::type = 0>
6492  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
6493  const bool add_prefix)
6494  {
6495  if ((std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)()) {
6496  if (add_prefix) {
6497  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('i')); // int8
6498  }
6499  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(n));
6500  } else if (static_cast<int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min)()) <= n and n <= static_cast<int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())) {
6501  if (add_prefix) {
6502  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('U')); // uint8
6503  }
6504  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(n));
6505  } else if ((std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)()) {
6506  if (add_prefix) {
6507  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('I')); // int16
6508  }
6509  write_number(static_cast<int16_t>(n));
6510  } else if ((std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)()) {
6511  if (add_prefix) {
6512  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('l')); // int32
6513  }
6514  write_number(static_cast<int32_t>(n));
6515  } else if ((std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)()) {
6516  if (add_prefix) {
6517  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('L')); // int64
6518  }
6519  write_number(static_cast<int64_t>(n));
6520  }
6521  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6522  else {
6523  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "number overflow serializing " + std::to_string(n)));
6524  }
6525  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6526  }
6527 
6537  char ubjson_prefix(const BasicJsonType& j) const noexcept
6538  {
6539  switch (j.type()) {
6540  case value_t::null:
6541  return 'Z';
6542 
6543  case value_t::boolean:
6544  return j.m_value.boolean ? 'T' : 'F';
6545 
6546  case value_t::number_integer: {
6547  if ((std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)()) {
6548  return 'i';
6549  } else if ((std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6550  return 'U';
6551  } else if ((std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)()) {
6552  return 'I';
6553  } else if ((std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)()) {
6554  return 'l';
6555  } else // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
6556  {
6557  return 'L';
6558  }
6559  }
6560 
6561  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
6562  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)()) {
6563  return 'i';
6564  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()) {
6565  return 'U';
6566  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)()) {
6567  return 'I';
6568  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)()) {
6569  return 'l';
6570  } else // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
6571  {
6572  return 'L';
6573  }
6574  }
6575 
6576  case value_t::number_float:
6577  return 'D';
6578 
6579  case value_t::string:
6580  return 'S';
6581 
6582  case value_t::array:
6583  return '[';
6584 
6585  case value_t::object:
6586  return '{';
6587 
6588  default: // discarded values
6589  return 'N';
6590  }
6591  }
6592 
6593  private:
6595  const bool is_little_endian = binary_reader<BasicJsonType>::little_endianess();
6596 
6598  output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
6599 };
6600 } // namespace detail
6601 } // namespace nlohmann

6658 template <typename Target, typename Source>
6659 Target reinterpret_bits(const Source source)
6660 {
6661  static_assert(sizeof(Target) == sizeof(Source), "size mismatch");
6662 
6663  Target target;
6664  std::memcpy(&target, &source, sizeof(Source));
6665  return target;
6666 }
6667 
6668 struct diyfp // f * 2^e
6669 {
6670  static constexpr int kPrecision = 64; // = q
6671 
6672  uint64_t f;
6673  int e;
6674 
6675  constexpr diyfp() noexcept : f(0), e(0) {}
6676  constexpr diyfp(uint64_t f_, int e_) noexcept : f(f_), e(e_) {}
6677 
6682  static diyfp sub(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
6683  {
6684  assert(x.e == y.e);
6685  assert(x.f >= y.f);
6686 
6687  return diyfp(x.f - y.f, x.e);
6688  }
6689 
6694  static diyfp mul(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
6695  {
6696  static_assert(kPrecision == 64, "internal error");
6697 
6698  // Computes:
6699  // f = round((x.f * y.f) / 2^q)
6700  // e = x.e + y.e + q
6701 
6702  // Emulate the 64-bit * 64-bit multiplication:
6703  //
6704  // p = u * v
6705  // = (u_lo + 2^32 u_hi) (v_lo + 2^32 v_hi)
6706  // = (u_lo v_lo ) + 2^32 ((u_lo v_hi ) + (u_hi v_lo )) + 2^64 (u_hi v_hi )
6707  // = (p0 ) + 2^32 ((p1 ) + (p2 )) + 2^64 (p3 )
6708  // = (p0_lo + 2^32 p0_hi) + 2^32 ((p1_lo + 2^32 p1_hi) + (p2_lo + 2^32 p2_hi)) + 2^64 (p3 )
6709  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo ) + 2^64 (p1_hi + p2_hi + p3)
6710  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q ) + 2^64 (H )
6711  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q_lo + 2^32 Q_hi ) + 2^64 (H )
6712  //
6713  // (Since Q might be larger than 2^32 - 1)
6714  //
6715  // = (p0_lo + 2^32 Q_lo) + 2^64 (Q_hi + H)
6716  //
6717  // (Q_hi + H does not overflow a 64-bit int)
6718  //
6719  // = p_lo + 2^64 p_hi
6720 
6721  const uint64_t u_lo = x.f & 0xFFFFFFFF;
6722  const uint64_t u_hi = x.f >> 32;
6723  const uint64_t v_lo = y.f & 0xFFFFFFFF;
6724  const uint64_t v_hi = y.f >> 32;
6725 
6726  const uint64_t p0 = u_lo * v_lo;
6727  const uint64_t p1 = u_lo * v_hi;
6728  const uint64_t p2 = u_hi * v_lo;
6729  const uint64_t p3 = u_hi * v_hi;
6730 
6731  const uint64_t p0_hi = p0 >> 32;
6732  const uint64_t p1_lo = p1 & 0xFFFFFFFF;
6733  const uint64_t p1_hi = p1 >> 32;
6734  const uint64_t p2_lo = p2 & 0xFFFFFFFF;
6735  const uint64_t p2_hi = p2 >> 32;
6736 
6737  uint64_t Q = p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo;
6738 
6739  // The full product might now be computed as
6740  //
6741  // p_hi = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32)
6742  // p_lo = p0_lo + (Q << 32)
6743  //
6744  // But in this particular case here, the full p_lo is not required.
6745  // Effectively we only need to add the highest bit in p_lo to p_hi (and
6746  // Q_hi + 1 does not overflow).
6747 
6748  Q += uint64_t{1} << (64 - 32 - 1); // round, ties up
6749 
6750  const uint64_t h = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32);
6751 
6752  return diyfp(h, x.e + y.e + 64);
6753  }
6754 
6759  static diyfp normalize(diyfp x) noexcept
6760  {
6761  assert(x.f != 0);
6762 
6763  while ((x.f >> 63) == 0) {
6764  x.f <<= 1;
6765  x.e--;
6766  }
6767 
6768  return x;
6769  }
6770 
6775  static diyfp normalize_to(const diyfp& x, const int target_exponent) noexcept
6776  {
6777  const int delta = x.e - target_exponent;
6778 
6779  assert(delta >= 0);
6780  assert(((x.f << delta) >> delta) == x.f);
6781 
6782  return diyfp(x.f << delta, target_exponent);
6783  }
6784 };
6785 
6786 struct boundaries {
6787  diyfp w;
6788  diyfp minus;
6789  diyfp plus;
6790 };
6791 
6798 template <typename FloatType>
6799 boundaries compute_boundaries(FloatType value)
6800 {
6801  assert(std::isfinite(value));
6802  assert(value > 0);
6803 
6804  // Convert the IEEE representation into a diyfp.
6805  //
6806  // If v is denormal:
6807  // value = 0.F * 2^(1 - bias) = ( F) * 2^(1 - bias - (p-1))
6808  // If v is normalized:
6809  // value = 1.F * 2^(E - bias) = (2^(p-1) + F) * 2^(E - bias - (p-1))
6810 
6811  static_assert(std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::is_iec559,
6812  "internal error: dtoa_short requires an IEEE-754 floating-point implementation");
6813 
6814  constexpr int kPrecision = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits; // = p (includes the hidden bit)
6815  constexpr int kBias = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_exponent - 1 + (kPrecision - 1);
6816  constexpr int kMinExp = 1 - kBias;
6817  constexpr uint64_t kHiddenBit = uint64_t{1} << (kPrecision - 1); // = 2^(p-1)
6818 
6819  using bits_type = typename std::conditional<kPrecision == 24, uint32_t, uint64_t>::type;
6820 
6821  const uint64_t bits = reinterpret_bits<bits_type>(value);
6822  const uint64_t E = bits >> (kPrecision - 1);
6823  const uint64_t F = bits & (kHiddenBit - 1);
6824 
6825  const bool is_denormal = (E == 0);
6826  const diyfp v = is_denormal
6827  ? diyfp(F, kMinExp)
6828  : diyfp(F + kHiddenBit, static_cast<int>(E) - kBias);
6829 
6830  // Compute the boundaries m- and m+ of the floating-point value
6831  // v = f * 2^e.
6832  //
6833  // Determine v- and v+, the floating-point predecessor and successor if v,
6834  // respectively.
6835  //
6836  // v- = v - 2^e if f != 2^(p-1) or e == e_min (A)
6837  // = v - 2^(e-1) if f == 2^(p-1) and e > e_min (B)
6838  //
6839  // v+ = v + 2^e
6840  //
6841  // Let m- = (v- + v) / 2 and m+ = (v + v+) / 2. All real numbers _strictly_
6842  // between m- and m+ round to v, regardless of how the input rounding
6843  // algorithm breaks ties.
6844  //
6845  // ---+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+--- (A)
6846  // v- m- v m+ v+
6847  //
6848  // -----------------+------+------+-------------+-------------+--- (B)
6849  // v- m- v m+ v+
6850 
6851  const bool lower_boundary_is_closer = (F == 0 and E > 1);
6852  const diyfp m_plus = diyfp(2 * v.f + 1, v.e - 1);
6853  const diyfp m_minus = lower_boundary_is_closer
6854  ? diyfp(4 * v.f - 1, v.e - 2) // (B)
6855  : diyfp(2 * v.f - 1, v.e - 1); // (A)
6856 
6857  // Determine the normalized w+ = m+.
6858  const diyfp w_plus = diyfp::normalize(m_plus);
6859 
6860  // Determine w- = m- such that e_(w-) = e_(w+).
6861  const diyfp w_minus = diyfp::normalize_to(m_minus, w_plus.e);
6862 
6863  return {diyfp::normalize(v), w_minus, w_plus};
6864 }
6865 
6866 // Given normalized diyfp w, Grisu needs to find a (normalized) cached
6867 // power-of-ten c, such that the exponent of the product c * w = f * 2^e lies
6868 // within a certain range [alpha, gamma] (Definition 3.2 from [1])
6869 //
6870 // alpha <= e = e_c + e_w + q <= gamma
6871 //
6872 // or
6873 //
6874 // f_c * f_w * 2^alpha <= f_c 2^(e_c) * f_w 2^(e_w) * 2^q
6875 // <= f_c * f_w * 2^gamma
6876 //
6877 // Since c and w are normalized, i.e. 2^(q-1) <= f < 2^q, this implies
6878 //
6879 // 2^(q-1) * 2^(q-1) * 2^alpha <= c * w * 2^q < 2^q * 2^q * 2^gamma
6880 //
6881 // or
6882 //
6883 // 2^(q - 2 + alpha) <= c * w < 2^(q + gamma)
6884 //
6885 // The choice of (alpha,gamma) determines the size of the table and the form of
6886 // the digit generation procedure. Using (alpha,gamma)=(-60,-32) works out well
6887 // in practice:
6888 //
6889 // The idea is to cut the number c * w = f * 2^e into two parts, which can be
6890 // processed independently: An integral part p1, and a fractional part p2:
6891 //
6892 // f * 2^e = ( (f div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (f mod 2^-e) ) * 2^e
6893 // = (f div 2^-e) + (f mod 2^-e) * 2^e
6894 // = p1 + p2 * 2^e
6895 //
6896 // The conversion of p1 into decimal form requires a series of divisions and
6897 // modulos by (a power of) 10. These operations are faster for 32-bit than for
6898 // 64-bit integers, so p1 should ideally fit into a 32-bit integer. This can be
6899 // achieved by choosing
6900 //
6901 // -e >= 32 or e <= -32 := gamma
6902 //
6903 // In order to convert the fractional part
6904 //
6905 // p2 * 2^e = p2 / 2^-e = d[-1] / 10^1 + d[-2] / 10^2 + ...
6906 //
6907 // into decimal form, the fraction is repeatedly multiplied by 10 and the digits
6908 // d[-i] are extracted in order:
6909 //
6910 // (10 * p2) div 2^-e = d[-1]
6911 // (10 * p2) mod 2^-e = d[-2] / 10^1 + ...
6912 //
6913 // The multiplication by 10 must not overflow. It is sufficient to choose
6914 //
6915 // 10 * p2 < 16 * p2 = 2^4 * p2 <= 2^64.
6916 //
6917 // Since p2 = f mod 2^-e < 2^-e,
6918 //
6919 // -e <= 60 or e >= -60 := alpha
6920 
6921 constexpr int kAlpha = -60;
6922 constexpr int kGamma = -32;
6923 
6924 struct cached_power // c = f * 2^e ~= 10^k
6925 {
6926  uint64_t f;
6927  int e;
6928  int k;
6929 };
6930 
6938 inline cached_power get_cached_power_for_binary_exponent(int e)
6939 {
6940  // Now
6941  //
6942  // alpha <= e_c + e + q <= gamma (1)
6943  // ==> f_c * 2^alpha <= c * 2^e * 2^q
6944  //
6945  // and since the c's are normalized, 2^(q-1) <= f_c,
6946  //
6947  // ==> 2^(q - 1 + alpha) <= c * 2^(e + q)
6948  // ==> 2^(alpha - e - 1) <= c
6949  //
6950  // If c were an exakt power of ten, i.e. c = 10^k, one may determine k as
6951  //
6952  // k = ceil( log_10( 2^(alpha - e - 1) ) )
6953  // = ceil( (alpha - e - 1) * log_10(2) )
6954  //
6955  // From the paper:
6956  // "In theory the result of the procedure could be wrong since c is rounded,
6957  // and the computation itself is approximated [...]. In practice, however,
6958  // this simple function is sufficient."
6959  //
6960  // For IEEE double precision floating-point numbers converted into
6961  // normalized diyfp's w = f * 2^e, with q = 64,
6962  //
6963  // e >= -1022 (min IEEE exponent)
6964  // -52 (p - 1)
6965  // -52 (p - 1, possibly normalize denormal IEEE numbers)
6966  // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
6967  // = -1137
6968  //
6969  // and
6970  //
6971  // e <= +1023 (max IEEE exponent)
6972  // -52 (p - 1)
6973  // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
6974  // = 960
6975  //
6976  // This binary exponent range [-1137,960] results in a decimal exponent
6977  // range [-307,324]. One does not need to store a cached power for each
6978  // k in this range. For each such k it suffices to find a cached power
6979  // such that the exponent of the product lies in [alpha,gamma].
6980  // This implies that the difference of the decimal exponents of adjacent
6981  // table entries must be less than or equal to
6982  //
6983  // floor( (gamma - alpha) * log_10(2) ) = 8.
6984  //
6985  // (A smaller distance gamma-alpha would require a larger table.)
6986 
6987  // NB:
6988  // Actually this function returns c, such that -60 <= e_c + e + 64 <= -34.
6989 
6990  constexpr int kCachedPowersSize = 79;
6991  constexpr int kCachedPowersMinDecExp = -300;
6992  constexpr int kCachedPowersDecStep = 8;
6993 
6994  static constexpr cached_power kCachedPowers[] =
6995  {
6996  {0xAB70FE17C79AC6CA, -1060, -300},
6997  {0xFF77B1FCBEBCDC4F, -1034, -292},
6998  {0xBE5691EF416BD60C, -1007, -284},
6999  {0x8DD01FAD907FFC3C, -980, -276},

7064  {0xBB764C4CA7A44410, 747, 244},
7065  {0x8BAB8EEFB6409C1A, 774, 252},
7066  {0xD01FEF10A657842C, 800, 260},
7067  {0x9B10A4E5E9913129, 827, 268},
7068  {0xE7109BFBA19C0C9D, 853, 276},
7069  {0xAC2820D9623BF429, 880, 284},
7070  {0x80444B5E7AA7CF85, 907, 292},
7071  {0xBF21E44003ACDD2D, 933, 300},
7072  {0x8E679C2F5E44FF8F, 960, 308},
7073  {0xD433179D9C8CB841, 986, 316},
7074  {0x9E19DB92B4E31BA9, 1013, 324},
7075  };
7076 
7077  // This computation gives exactly the same results for k as
7078  // k = ceil((kAlpha - e - 1) * 0.30102999566398114)
7079  // for |e| <= 1500, but doesn't require floating-point operations.
7080  // NB: log_10(2) ~= 78913 / 2^18
7081  assert(e >= -1500);
7082  assert(e <= 1500);
7083  const int f = kAlpha - e - 1;
7084  const int k = (f * 78913) / (1 << 18) + (f > 0);
7085 
7086  const int index = (-kCachedPowersMinDecExp + k + (kCachedPowersDecStep - 1)) / kCachedPowersDecStep;
7087  assert(index >= 0);
7088  assert(index < kCachedPowersSize);
7089  static_cast<void>(kCachedPowersSize); // Fix warning.
7090 
7091  const cached_power cached = kCachedPowers[index];
7092  assert(kAlpha <= cached.e + e + 64);
7093  assert(kGamma >= cached.e + e + 64);
7094 
7095  return cached;
7096 }
7097 
7102 inline int find_largest_pow10(const uint32_t n, uint32_t& pow10)
7103 {
7104  // LCOV_EXCL_START
7105  if (n >= 1000000000) {
7106  pow10 = 1000000000;
7107  return 10;
7108  }
7109  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
7110  else if (n >= 100000000) {
7111  pow10 = 100000000;
7112  return 9;
7113  } else if (n >= 10000000) {
7114  pow10 = 10000000;
7115  return 8;
7116  } else if (n >= 1000000) {
7117  pow10 = 1000000;
7118  return 7;
7119  } else if (n >= 100000) {
7120  pow10 = 100000;
7121  return 6;
7122  } else if (n >= 10000) {
7123  pow10 = 10000;
7124  return 5;
7125  } else if (n >= 1000) {
7126  pow10 = 1000;
7127  return 4;
7128  } else if (n >= 100) {
7129  pow10 = 100;
7130  return 3;
7131  } else if (n >= 10) {
7132  pow10 = 10;
7133  return 2;
7134  } else {
7135  pow10 = 1;
7136  return 1;
7137  }
7138 }
7139 
7140 inline void grisu2_round(char* buf, int len, uint64_t dist, uint64_t delta,
7141  uint64_t rest, uint64_t ten_k)
7142 {
7143  assert(len >= 1);
7144  assert(dist <= delta);
7145  assert(rest <= delta);
7146  assert(ten_k > 0);
7147 
7148  // <--------------------------- delta ---->
7149  // <---- dist --------->
7150  // --------------[------------------+-------------------]--------------
7151  // M- w M+
7152  //
7153  // ten_k
7154  // <------>
7155  // <---- rest ---->
7156  // --------------[------------------+----+--------------]--------------
7157  // w V
7158  // = buf * 10^k
7159  //
7160  // ten_k represents a unit-in-the-last-place in the decimal representation
7161  // stored in buf.
7162  // Decrement buf by ten_k while this takes buf closer to w.
7163 
7164  // The tests are written in this order to avoid overflow in unsigned
7165  // integer arithmetic.
7166 
7167  while (rest < dist and delta - rest >= ten_k and (rest + ten_k < dist or dist - rest > rest + ten_k - dist)) {
7168  assert(buf[len - 1] != '0');
7169  buf[len - 1]--;
7170  rest += ten_k;
7171  }
7172 }
7173 
7178 inline void grisu2_digit_gen(char* buffer, int& length, int& decimal_exponent,
7179  diyfp M_minus, diyfp w, diyfp M_plus)
7180 {
7181  static_assert(kAlpha >= -60, "internal error");
7182  static_assert(kGamma <= -32, "internal error");
7183 
7184  // Generates the digits (and the exponent) of a decimal floating-point
7185  // number V = buffer * 10^decimal_exponent in the range [M-, M+]. The diyfp's
7186  // w, M- and M+ share the same exponent e, which satisfies alpha <= e <= gamma.
7187  //
7188  // <--------------------------- delta ---->
7189  // <---- dist --------->
7190  // --------------[------------------+-------------------]--------------
7191  // M- w M+
7192  //
7193  // Grisu2 generates the digits of M+ from left to right and stops as soon as
7194  // V is in [M-,M+].
7195 
7196  assert(M_plus.e >= kAlpha);
7197  assert(M_plus.e <= kGamma);
7198 
7199  uint64_t delta = diyfp::sub(M_plus, M_minus).f; // (significand of (M+ - M-), implicit exponent is e)
7200  uint64_t dist = diyfp::sub(M_plus, w).f; // (significand of (M+ - w ), implicit exponent is e)
7201 
7202  // Split M+ = f * 2^e into two parts p1 and p2 (note: e < 0):
7203  //
7204  // M+ = f * 2^e
7205  // = ((f div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (f mod 2^-e)) * 2^e
7206  // = ((p1 ) * 2^-e + (p2 )) * 2^e
7207  // = p1 + p2 * 2^e
7208 
7209  const diyfp one(uint64_t{1} << -M_plus.e, M_plus.e);
7210 
7211  uint32_t p1 = static_cast<uint32_t>(M_plus.f >> -one.e); // p1 = f div 2^-e (Since -e >= 32, p1 fits into a 32-bit int.)
7212  uint64_t p2 = M_plus.f & (one.f - 1); // p2 = f mod 2^-e
7213 
7214  // 1)
7215  //
7216  // Generate the digits of the integral part p1 = d[n-1]...d[1]d[0]
7217 
7218  assert(p1 > 0);
7219 
7220  uint32_t pow10;
7221  const int k = find_largest_pow10(p1, pow10);
7222 
7223  // 10^(k-1) <= p1 < 10^k, pow10 = 10^(k-1)
7224  //
7225  // p1 = (p1 div 10^(k-1)) * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1))
7226  // = (d[k-1] ) * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1))
7227  //
7228  // M+ = p1 + p2 * 2^e
7229  // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1)) + p2 * 2^e
7230  // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + ((p1 mod 10^(k-1)) * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e
7231  // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + ( rest) * 2^e
7232  //
7233  // Now generate the digits d[n] of p1 from left to right (n = k-1,...,0)
7234  //
7235  // p1 = d[k-1]...d[n] * 10^n + d[n-1]...d[0]
7236  //
7237  // but stop as soon as
7238  //
7239  // rest * 2^e = (d[n-1]...d[0] * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
7240 
7241  int n = k;
7242  while (n > 0) {
7243  // Invariants:
7244  // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (p1 + p2 * 2^e) (buffer = 0 for n = k)
7245  // pow10 = 10^(n-1) <= p1 < 10^n
7246  //
7247  const uint32_t d = p1 / pow10; // d = p1 div 10^(n-1)
7248  const uint32_t r = p1 % pow10; // r = p1 mod 10^(n-1)
7249  //
7250  // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (d * 10^(n-1) + r) + p2 * 2^e
7251  // = (buffer * 10 + d) * 10^(n-1) + (r + p2 * 2^e)
7252  //
7253  assert(d <= 9);
7254  buffer[length++] = static_cast<char>('0' + d); // buffer := buffer * 10 + d
7255  //
7256  // M+ = buffer * 10^(n-1) + (r + p2 * 2^e)
7257  //
7258  p1 = r;
7259  n--;
7260  //
7261  // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (p1 + p2 * 2^e)
7262  // pow10 = 10^n
7263  //
7264 
7265  // Now check if enough digits have been generated.
7266  // Compute
7267  //
7268  // p1 + p2 * 2^e = (p1 * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e = rest * 2^e
7269  //
7270  // Note:
7271  // Since rest and delta share the same exponent e, it suffices to
7272  // compare the significands.
7273  const uint64_t rest = (uint64_t{p1} << -one.e) + p2;
7274  if (rest <= delta) {
7275  // V = buffer * 10^n, with M- <= V <= M+.
7276 
7277  decimal_exponent += n;
7278 
7279  // We may now just stop. But instead look if the buffer could be
7280  // decremented to bring V closer to w.
7281  //
7282  // pow10 = 10^n is now 1 ulp in the decimal representation V.
7283  // The rounding procedure works with diyfp's with an implicit
7284  // exponent of e.
7285  //
7286  // 10^n = (10^n * 2^-e) * 2^e = ulp * 2^e
7287  //
7288  const uint64_t ten_n = uint64_t{pow10} << -one.e;
7289  grisu2_round(buffer, length, dist, delta, rest, ten_n);
7290 
7291  return;
7292  }
7293 
7294  pow10 /= 10;
7295  //
7296  // pow10 = 10^(n-1) <= p1 < 10^n
7297  // Invariants restored.
7298  }
7299 
7300  // 2)
7301  //
7302  // The digits of the integral part have been generated:
7303  //
7304  // M+ = d[k-1]...d[1]d[0] + p2 * 2^e
7305  // = buffer + p2 * 2^e
7306  //
7307  // Now generate the digits of the fractional part p2 * 2^e.
7308  //
7309  // Note:
7310  // No decimal point is generated: the exponent is adjusted instead.
7311  //
7312  // p2 actually represents the fraction
7313  //
7314  // p2 * 2^e
7315  // = p2 / 2^-e
7316  // = d[-1] / 10^1 + d[-2] / 10^2 + ...
7317  //
7318  // Now generate the digits d[-m] of p1 from left to right (m = 1,2,...)
7319  //
7320  // p2 * 2^e = d[-1]d[-2]...d[-m] * 10^-m
7321  // + 10^-m * (d[-m-1] / 10^1 + d[-m-2] / 10^2 + ...)
7322  //
7323  // using
7324  //
7325  // 10^m * p2 = ((10^m * p2) div 2^-e) * 2^-e + ((10^m * p2) mod 2^-e)
7326  // = ( d) * 2^-e + ( r)
7327  //
7328  // or
7329  // 10^m * p2 * 2^e = d + r * 2^e
7330  //
7331  // i.e.
7332  //
7333  // M+ = buffer + p2 * 2^e
7334  // = buffer + 10^-m * (d + r * 2^e)
7335  // = (buffer * 10^m + d) * 10^-m + 10^-m * r * 2^e
7336  //
7337  // and stop as soon as 10^-m * r * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
7338 
7339  assert(p2 > delta);
7340 
7341  int m = 0;
7342  for (;;) {
7343  // Invariant:
7344  // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (d[-m-1] / 10 + d[-m-2] / 10^2 + ...) * 2^e
7345  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (p2 ) * 2^e
7346  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (10 * p2) ) * 2^e
7347  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * ((10*p2 div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (10*p2 mod 2^-e)) * 2^e
7348  //
7349  assert(p2 <= UINT64_MAX / 10);
7350  p2 *= 10;
7351  const uint64_t d = p2 >> -one.e; // d = (10 * p2) div 2^-e
7352  const uint64_t r = p2 & (one.f - 1); // r = (10 * p2) mod 2^-e
7353  //
7354  // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (d * 2^-e + r) * 2^e
7355  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (d + r * 2^e))
7356  // = (buffer * 10 + d) * 10^(-m-1) + 10^(-m-1) * r * 2^e
7357  //
7358  assert(d <= 9);
7359  buffer[length++] = static_cast<char>('0' + d); // buffer := buffer * 10 + d
7360  //
7361  // M+ = buffer * 10^(-m-1) + 10^(-m-1) * r * 2^e
7362  //
7363  p2 = r;
7364  m++;
7365  //
7366  // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * p2 * 2^e
7367  // Invariant restored.
7368 
7369  // Check if enough digits have been generated.
7370  //
7371  // 10^-m * p2 * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
7372  // p2 * 2^e <= 10^m * delta * 2^e
7373  // p2 <= 10^m * delta
7374  delta *= 10;
7375  dist *= 10;
7376  if (p2 <= delta) {
7377  break;
7378  }
7379  }
7380 
7381  // V = buffer * 10^-m, with M- <= V <= M+.
7382 
7383  decimal_exponent -= m;
7384 
7385  // 1 ulp in the decimal representation is now 10^-m.
7386  // Since delta and dist are now scaled by 10^m, we need to do the
7387  // same with ulp in order to keep the units in sync.
7388  //
7389  // 10^m * 10^-m = 1 = 2^-e * 2^e = ten_m * 2^e
7390  //
7391  const uint64_t ten_m = one.f;
7392  grisu2_round(buffer, length, dist, delta, p2, ten_m);
7393 
7394  // By construction this algorithm generates the shortest possible decimal
7395  // number (Loitsch, Theorem 6.2) which rounds back to w.
7396  // For an input number of precision p, at least
7397  //
7398  // N = 1 + ceil(p * log_10(2))
7399  //
7400  // decimal digits are sufficient to identify all binary floating-point
7401  // numbers (Matula, "In-and-Out conversions").
7402  // This implies that the algorithm does not produce more than N decimal
7403  // digits.
7404  //
7405  // N = 17 for p = 53 (IEEE double precision)
7406  // N = 9 for p = 24 (IEEE single precision)
7407 }
7408 
7414 inline void grisu2(char* buf, int& len, int& decimal_exponent,
7415  diyfp m_minus, diyfp v, diyfp m_plus)
7416 {
7417  assert(m_plus.e == m_minus.e);
7418  assert(m_plus.e == v.e);
7419 
7420  // --------(-----------------------+-----------------------)-------- (A)
7421  // m- v m+
7422  //
7423  // --------------------(-----------+-----------------------)-------- (B)
7424  // m- v m+
7425  //
7426  // First scale v (and m- and m+) such that the exponent is in the range
7427  // [alpha, gamma].
7428 
7429  const cached_power cached = get_cached_power_for_binary_exponent(m_plus.e);
7430 
7431  const diyfp c_minus_k(cached.f, cached.e); // = c ~= 10^-k
7432 
7433  // The exponent of the products is = v.e + c_minus_k.e + q and is in the range [alpha,gamma]
7434  const diyfp w = diyfp::mul(v, c_minus_k);
7435  const diyfp w_minus = diyfp::mul(m_minus, c_minus_k);
7436  const diyfp w_plus = diyfp::mul(m_plus, c_minus_k);
7437 
7438  // ----(---+---)---------------(---+---)---------------(---+---)----
7439  // w- w w+
7440  // = c*m- = c*v = c*m+
7441  //
7442  // diyfp::mul rounds its result and c_minus_k is approximated too. w, w- and
7443  // w+ are now off by a small amount.
7444  // In fact:
7445  //
7446  // w - v * 10^k < 1 ulp
7447  //
7448  // To account for this inaccuracy, add resp. subtract 1 ulp.
7449  //
7450  // --------+---[---------------(---+---)---------------]---+--------
7451  // w- M- w M+ w+
7452  //
7453  // Now any number in [M-, M+] (bounds included) will round to w when input,
7454  // regardless of how the input rounding algorithm breaks ties.
7455  //
7456  // And digit_gen generates the shortest possible such number in [M-, M+].
7457  // Note that this does not mean that Grisu2 always generates the shortest
7458  // possible number in the interval (m-, m+).
7459  const diyfp M_minus(w_minus.f + 1, w_minus.e);
7460  const diyfp M_plus(w_plus.f - 1, w_plus.e);
7461 
7462  decimal_exponent = -cached.k; // = -(-k) = k
7463 
7464  grisu2_digit_gen(buf, len, decimal_exponent, M_minus, w, M_plus);
7465 }
7466 
7472 template <typename FloatType>
7473 void grisu2(char* buf, int& len, int& decimal_exponent, FloatType value)
7474 {
7475  static_assert(diyfp::kPrecision >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits + 3,
7476  "internal error: not enough precision");
7477 
7478  assert(std::isfinite(value));
7479  assert(value > 0);
7480 
7481 // If the neighbors (and boundaries) of 'value' are always computed for double-precision
7482 // numbers, all float's can be recovered using strtod (and strtof). However, the resulting
7483 // decimal representations are not exactly "short".
7484 //
7485 // The documentation for 'std::to_chars' (http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/to_chars)
7486 // says "value is converted to a string as if by std::sprintf in the default ("C") locale"
7487 // and since sprintf promotes float's to double's, I think this is exactly what 'std::to_chars'
7488 // does.
7489 // On the other hand, the documentation for 'std::to_chars' requires that "parsing the
7490 // representation using the corresponding std::from_chars function recovers value exactly". That
7491 // indicates that single precision floating-point numbers should be recovered using
7492 // 'std::strtof'.
7493 //
7494 // NB: If the neighbors are computed for single-precision numbers, there is a single float
7495 // (7.0385307e-26f) which can't be recovered using strtod. The resulting double precision
7496 // value is off by 1 ulp.
7497 #if 0
7498  const boundaries w = compute_boundaries(static_cast<double>(value));
7499 #else
7500  const boundaries w = compute_boundaries(value);
7501 #endif
7502 
7503  grisu2(buf, len, decimal_exponent, w.minus, w.w, w.plus);
7504 }
7505 
7511 inline char* append_exponent(char* buf, int e)
7512 {
7513  assert(e > -1000);
7514  assert(e < 1000);
7515 
7516  if (e < 0) {
7517  e = -e;
7518  *buf++ = '-';
7519  } else {
7520  *buf++ = '+';
7521  }
7522 
7523  uint32_t k = static_cast<uint32_t>(e);
7524  if (k < 10) {
7525  // Always print at least two digits in the exponent.
7526  // This is for compatibility with printf("%g").
7527  *buf++ = '0';
7528  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
7529  } else if (k < 100) {
7530  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 10);
7531  k %= 10;
7532  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
7533  } else {
7534  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 100);
7535  k %= 100;
7536  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 10);
7537  k %= 10;
7538  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
7539  }
7540 
7541  return buf;
7542 }
7543 
7553 inline char* format_buffer(char* buf, int len, int decimal_exponent,
7554  int min_exp, int max_exp)
7555 {
7556  assert(min_exp < 0);
7557  assert(max_exp > 0);
7558 
7559  const int k = len;
7560  const int n = len + decimal_exponent;
7561 
7562  // v = buf * 10^(n-k)
7563  // k is the length of the buffer (number of decimal digits)
7564  // n is the position of the decimal point relative to the start of the buffer.
7565 
7566  if (k <= n and n <= max_exp) {
7567  // digits[000]
7568  // len <= max_exp + 2
7569 
7570  std::memset(buf + k, '0', static_cast<size_t>(n - k));
7571  // Make it look like a floating-point number (#362, #378)
7572  buf[n + 0] = '.';
7573  buf[n + 1] = '0';
7574  return buf + (n + 2);
7575  }
7576 
7577  if (0 < n and n <= max_exp) {
7578  // dig.its
7579  // len <= max_digits10 + 1
7580 
7581  assert(k > n);
7582 
7583  std::memmove(buf + (n + 1), buf + n, static_cast<size_t>(k - n));
7584  buf[n] = '.';
7585  return buf + (k + 1);
7586  }
7587 
7588  if (min_exp < n and n <= 0) {
7589  // 0.[000]digits
7590  // len <= 2 + (-min_exp - 1) + max_digits10
7591 
7592  std::memmove(buf + (2 + -n), buf, static_cast<size_t>(k));
7593  buf[0] = '0';
7594  buf[1] = '.';
7595  std::memset(buf + 2, '0', static_cast<size_t>(-n));
7596  return buf + (2 + (-n) + k);
7597  }
7598 
7599  if (k == 1) {
7600  // dE+123
7601  // len <= 1 + 5
7602 
7603  buf += 1;
7604  } else {
7605  // d.igitsE+123
7606  // len <= max_digits10 + 1 + 5
7607 
7608  std::memmove(buf + 2, buf + 1, static_cast<size_t>(k - 1));
7609  buf[1] = '.';
7610  buf += 1 + k;
7611  }
7612 
7613  *buf++ = 'e';
7614  return append_exponent(buf, n - 1);
7615 }
7616 
7617 } // namespace dtoa_impl
7618 
7629 template <typename FloatType>
7630 char* to_chars(char* first, char* last, FloatType value)
7631 {
7632  static_cast<void>(last); // maybe unused - fix warning
7633  assert(std::isfinite(value));
7634 
7635  // Use signbit(value) instead of (value < 0) since signbit works for -0.
7636  if (std::signbit(value)) {
7637  value = -value;
7638  *first++ = '-';
7639  }
7640 
7641  if (value == 0) // +-0
7642  {
7643  *first++ = '0';
7644  // Make it look like a floating-point number (#362, #378)
7645  *first++ = '.';
7646  *first++ = '0';
7647  return first;
7648  }
7649 
7650  assert(last - first >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
7651 
7652  // Compute v = buffer * 10^decimal_exponent.
7653  // The decimal digits are stored in the buffer, which needs to be interpreted
7654  // as an unsigned decimal integer.
7655  // len is the length of the buffer, i.e. the number of decimal digits.
7656  int len = 0;
7657  int decimal_exponent = 0;
7658  dtoa_impl::grisu2(first, len, decimal_exponent, value);
7659 
7660  assert(len <= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
7661 
7662  // Format the buffer like printf("%.*g", prec, value)
7663  constexpr int kMinExp = -4;
7664  // Use digits10 here to increase compatibility with version 2.
7665  constexpr int kMaxExp = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits10;
7666 
7667  assert(last - first >= kMaxExp + 2);
7668  assert(last - first >= 2 + (-kMinExp - 1) + std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
7669  assert(last - first >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10 + 6);
7670 
7671  return dtoa_impl::format_buffer(first, len, decimal_exponent, kMinExp, kMaxExp);
7672 }
7673 
7674 } // namespace detail
7675 } // namespace nlohmann

7687 namespace detail
